78 // Creates an array out of the arguments without hardcoding the exact number of
79 // arguments.
80 template <typename... T>
81 constexpr auto CreateArray(T... elements) {
82  std::array result = {elements...};
83  return result;
84 }
85 
86 // Concatenate arrays into one array in compile-time.
87 template <typename T, size_t... N>
88 constexpr auto ConcatArrays(std::array<T, N>... array) {
89  constexpr size_t kNumArrays = sizeof...(array);
90  std::array<T*, kNumArrays> kArrays = {&array[0]...};
91  constexpr size_t kLengths[kNumArrays] = {array.size()...};
92  constexpr size_t kSumOfLengths = (... + array.size());
93 
94  std::array<T, kSumOfLengths> result = {0};
95  size_t result_index = 0;
96  for (size_t arr = 0; arr < kNumArrays; arr++) {
97  for (size_t pos = 0; pos < kLengths[arr]; pos++) {
98  result[result_index++] = kArrays[arr][pos];
99  }
100  }
101  return result;
102 }

104 class DataRange {
105  // data_ is used for general random values for fuzzing.
106  base::Vector<const uint8_t> data_;
107  // The RNG is used for generating random values (i32.consts etc.) for which
108  // the quality of the input is less important.
109  base::RandomNumberGenerator rng_;
110 
111  public:
112  explicit DataRange(base::Vector<const uint8_t> data, int64_t seed = -1)
113  : data_(data), rng_(seed == -1 ? get<int64_t>() : seed) {}
114  DataRange(const DataRange&) = delete;
115  DataRange& operator=(const DataRange&) = delete;
116  // To generate wasm simd opcodes that can be merged into 256-bit in revec
117  // phase.
118  DataRange clone() const { return DataRange(data_, rng_.initial_seed()); }
119 
120  // Don't accidentally pass DataRange by value. This will reuse bytes and might
121  // lead to OOM because the end might not be reached.
122  // Define move constructor and move assignment, disallow copy constructor and
123  // copy assignment (below).
124  DataRange(DataRange&& other) V8_NOEXCEPT : data_(other.data_),
125  rng_(other.rng_) {
126  other.data_ = {};
127  }
128  DataRange& operator=(DataRange&& other) V8_NOEXCEPT {
129  data_ = other.data_;
130  rng_ = other.rng_;
131  other.data_ = {};
132  return *this;
133  }
134 
135  size_t size() const { return data_.size(); }
136 
137  DataRange split() {
138  // As we might split many times, only use 2 bytes if the data size is large.
139  uint16_t random_choice = data_.size() > std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max()
140  ? get<uint16_t>()
141  : get<uint8_t>();
142  uint16_t num_bytes = random_choice % std::max(size_t{1}, data_.size());
143  int64_t new_seed = rng_.initial_seed() ^ rng_.NextInt64();
144  DataRange split(data_.SubVector(0, num_bytes), new_seed);
145  data_ += num_bytes;
146  return split;
147  }
148 
149  template <typename T, size_t max_bytes = sizeof(T)>
150  T getPseudoRandom() {
151  static_assert(!std::is_same_v<T, bool>, "bool needs special handling");
152  static_assert(max_bytes <= sizeof(T));
153  // Special handling for signed integers: Calling getPseudoRandom<int32_t, 1>
154  // () should be equal to getPseudoRandom<int8_t>(). (The NextBytes() below
155  // does not achieve that due to depending on endianness and either never
156  // generating negative values or filling in the highest significant bits
157  // which would be unexpected).
158  if constexpr (std::is_integral_v<T> && std::is_signed_v<T>) {
159  switch (max_bytes) {
160  case 1:
161  return static_cast<int8_t>(getPseudoRandom<uint8_t>());
162  case 2:
163  return static_cast<int16_t>(getPseudoRandom<uint16_t>());
164  case 4:
165  return static_cast<int32_t>(getPseudoRandom<uint32_t>());
166  default:
167  return static_cast<T>(
168  getPseudoRandom<std::make_unsigned_t<T>, max_bytes>());
169  }
170  }
171 
172  T result{};
173  rng_.NextBytes(&result, max_bytes);
174  return result;
175  }
176 
177  template <typename T>
178  T get() {
179  // Bool needs special handling (see template specialization below).
180  static_assert(!std::is_same_v<T, bool>, "bool needs special handling");
181 
182  // We want to support the case where we have less than sizeof(T) bytes
183  // remaining in the slice. We'll just use what we have, so we get a bit of
184  // randomness when there are still some bytes left. If size == 0, get<T>()
185  // returns the type's value-initialized value.
186  const size_t num_bytes = std::min(sizeof(T), data_.size());
187  T result{};
188  memcpy(&result, data_.begin(), num_bytes);
189  data_ += num_bytes;
190  return result;
191  }
192 };
193 
194 // Explicit specialization must be defined outside of class body.
195 template <>
196 bool DataRange::get() {
197  // The general implementation above is not instantiable for bool, as that
198  // would cause undefinied behaviour when memcpy'ing random bytes to the
199  // bool. This can result in different observable side effects when invoking
200  // get<bool> between debug and release version, which eventually makes the
201  // code output different as well as raising various unrecoverable errors on
202  // runtime.
203  // Hence we specialize get<bool> to consume a full byte and use the least
204  // significant bit only (0 == false, 1 == true).
205  return get<uint8_t>() % 2;
206 }

208 enum IncludeNumericTypes {
209  kIncludeNumericTypes = true,
210  kExcludeNumericTypes = false
211 };
212 enum IncludePackedTypes {
213  kIncludePackedTypes = true,
214  kExcludePackedTypes = false
215 };
216 enum IncludeAllGenerics {
217  kIncludeAllGenerics = true,
218  kExcludeSomeGenerics = false
219 };
220 enum IncludeS128 { kIncludeS128 = true, kExcludeS128 = false };
221 
222 // Chooses one `ValueType` randomly based on `options` and the enums specified
223 // above.
224 ValueType GetValueTypeHelper(WasmModuleGenerationOptions options,
225  DataRange* data, uint32_t num_nullable_types,
226  uint32_t num_non_nullable_types,
227  IncludeNumericTypes include_numeric_types,
228  IncludePackedTypes include_packed_types,
229  IncludeAllGenerics include_all_generics,
230  IncludeS128 include_s128 = kIncludeS128) {
231  // Create and fill a vector of potential types to choose from.
232  base::SmallVector<ValueType, 32> types;
233 
234  // Numeric non-wasmGC types.
235  if (include_numeric_types) {
236  // Many "general-purpose" instructions return i32, so give that a higher
237  // probability (such as 3x).
238  types.insert(types.end(),
239  {kWasmI32, kWasmI32, kWasmI32, kWasmI64, kWasmF32, kWasmF64});
240 
241  // SIMD type.
242  if (options.generate_simd() && include_s128) {
243  types.push_back(kWasmS128);
244  }
245  }
246 
247  // The MVP types: apart from numeric types, contains only the non-nullable
248  // funcRef. We don't add externRef, because for externRef globals we generate
249  // initialiser expressions where we need wasmGC types. Also, externRef is not
250  // really useful for the MVP fuzzer, as there is nothing that we could
251  // generate.
252  types.push_back(kWasmFuncRef);
253 
254  // WasmGC types (including user-defined types).
255  // Decide if the return type will be nullable or not.
256  const bool nullable = options.generate_wasm_gc() ? data->get<bool>() : false;
257 
258  if (options.generate_wasm_gc()) {
259  types.push_back(kWasmI31Ref);
260 
261  if (include_numeric_types && include_packed_types) {
262  types.insert(types.end(), {kWasmI8, kWasmI16});
263  }
264 
265  if (nullable) {
266  types.insert(types.end(),
267  {kWasmNullRef, kWasmNullExternRef, kWasmNullFuncRef});
268  }
269  if (nullable || include_all_generics) {
270  types.insert(types.end(), {kWasmStructRef, kWasmArrayRef, kWasmAnyRef,
271  kWasmEqRef, kWasmExternRef});
272  }
273  }
274 
275  // The last index of user-defined types allowed is different based on the
276  // nullability of the output. User-defined types are function signatures or
277  // structs and arrays (in case of wasmGC).
278  const uint32_t num_user_defined_types =
279  nullable ? num_nullable_types : num_non_nullable_types;
280 
281  // Conceptually, user-defined types are added to the end of the list. Pick a
282  // random one among them.
283  uint32_t chosen_id =
284  data->get<uint8_t>() % (types.size() + num_user_defined_types);
285 
286  Nullability nullability = nullable ? kNullable : kNonNullable;
287 
288  if (chosen_id >= types.size()) {
289  // Return user-defined type.
290  return ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
291  ModuleTypeIndex{chosen_id - static_cast<uint32_t>(types.size())},
292  nullability, kNotShared, RefTypeKind::kOther /* unknown */);
293  }
294  // If returning a reference type, fix its nullability according to {nullable}.
295  if (types[chosen_id].is_reference()) {
296  return ValueType::RefMaybeNull(types[chosen_id].heap_type(), nullability);
297  }
298  // Otherwise, just return the picked type.
299  return types[chosen_id];
300 }
301 
302 ValueType GetValueType(WasmModuleGenerationOptions options, DataRange* data,
303  uint32_t num_types) {
304  return GetValueTypeHelper(options, data, num_types, num_types,
305  kIncludeNumericTypes, kExcludePackedTypes,
306  kIncludeAllGenerics);
307 }
308 
309 void GeneratePassiveDataSegment(DataRange* range, WasmModuleBuilder* builder) {
310  int length = range->get<uint8_t>() % 65;
311  ZoneVector<uint8_t> data(length, builder->zone());
312  for (int i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
313  data[i] = range->getPseudoRandom<uint8_t>();
314  }
315  builder->AddPassiveDataSegment(data.data(),
316  static_cast<uint32_t>(data.size()));
317 }
318 
319 uint32_t GenerateRefTypeElementSegment(DataRange* range,
320  WasmModuleBuilder* builder,
321  ValueType element_type) {
322  DCHECK(element_type.is_object_reference());
323  DCHECK(element_type.has_index());
324  WasmModuleBuilder::WasmElemSegment segment(
325  builder->zone(), element_type, false,
326  WasmInitExpr::RefNullConst(element_type.heap_type()));
327  size_t element_count = range->get<uint8_t>() % 11;
328  for (size_t i = 0; i < element_count; ++i) {
329  segment.entries.emplace_back(
330  WasmModuleBuilder::WasmElemSegment::Entry::kRefNullEntry,
331  element_type.ref_index().index);
332  }
333  return builder->AddElementSegment(std::move(segment));
334 }
335 
336 std::vector<ValueType> GenerateTypes(WasmModuleGenerationOptions options,
337  DataRange* data, uint32_t num_ref_types) {
338  std::vector<ValueType> types;
339  int num_params = int{data->get<uint8_t>()} % (kMaxParameters + 1);
340  types.reserve(num_params);
341  for (int i = 0; i < num_params; ++i) {
342  types.push_back(GetValueType(options, data, num_ref_types));
343  }
344  return types;
345 }
346 
347 FunctionSig* CreateSignature(Zone* zone,
348  base::Vector<const ValueType> param_types,
349  base::Vector<const ValueType> return_types) {
350  FunctionSig::Builder builder(zone, return_types.size(), param_types.size());
351  for (auto& type : param_types) {
352  builder.AddParam(type);
353  }
354  for (auto& type : return_types) {
355  builder.AddReturn(type);
356  }
357  return builder.Get();
358 }

360 class BodyGen;
361 using GenerateFn = void (BodyGen::*)(DataRange*);
362 using GenerateFnWithHeap = bool (BodyGen::*)(HeapType, DataRange*, Nullability);
363 
364 // GeneratorAlternativesPerOption allows to statically precompute the generator
365 // arrays for different {WasmModuleGenerationOptions}.
366 template <size_t kNumMVP, size_t kAdditionalSimd, size_t kAdditionalWasmGC>
367 class GeneratorAlternativesPerOption {
368  static constexpr size_t kNumSimd = kNumMVP + kAdditionalSimd;
369  static constexpr size_t kNumWasmGC = kNumMVP + kAdditionalWasmGC;
370  static constexpr size_t kNumAll = kNumSimd + kAdditionalWasmGC;
371 
372  public:
373  constexpr GeneratorAlternativesPerOption(
374  std::array<GenerateFn, kNumMVP> mvp,
375  std::array<GenerateFn, kAdditionalSimd> simd,
376  std::array<GenerateFn, kAdditionalWasmGC> wasmgc)
377  : mvp_(mvp),
378  simd_(ConcatArrays(mvp, simd)),
379  wasmgc_(ConcatArrays(mvp, wasmgc)),
380  all_(ConcatArrays(mvp, ConcatArrays(simd, wasmgc))) {}
381 
382  constexpr base::Vector<const GenerateFn> GetAlternatives(
383  WasmModuleGenerationOptions options) const {
384  switch (options.ToIntegral()) {
385  case 0: // 0
386  return base::VectorOf(mvp_);
387  case 1 << kGenerateSIMD: // 1
388  return base::VectorOf(simd_);
389  case 1 << kGenerateWasmGC: // 2
390  return base::VectorOf(wasmgc_);
391  case (1 << kGenerateSIMD) | (1 << kGenerateWasmGC): // 3
392  return base::VectorOf(all_);
393  }
394  UNREACHABLE();
395  }
396 
397  private:
398  const std::array<GenerateFn, kNumMVP> mvp_;
399  const std::array<GenerateFn, kNumSimd> simd_;
400  const std::array<GenerateFn, kNumWasmGC> wasmgc_;
401  const std::array<GenerateFn, kNumAll> all_;
402 };
403 
404 // Deduction guide for the GeneratorAlternativesPerOption template.
405 template <size_t kNumMVP, size_t kAdditionalSimd, size_t kAdditionalWasmGC>
406 GeneratorAlternativesPerOption(std::array<GenerateFn, kNumMVP>,
407  std::array<GenerateFn, kAdditionalSimd>,
408  std::array<GenerateFn, kAdditionalWasmGC>)
409  -> GeneratorAlternativesPerOption<kNumMVP, kAdditionalSimd,
410  kAdditionalWasmGC>;

412 class BodyGen {
413  template <WasmOpcode Op, ValueKind... Args>
414  void op(DataRange* data) {
415  Generate<Args...>(data);
416  builder_->Emit(Op);
417  }
418 
419  class V8_NODISCARD BlockScope {
420  public:
421  BlockScope(BodyGen* gen, WasmOpcode block_type,
422  base::Vector<const ValueType> param_types,
423  base::Vector<const ValueType> result_types,
424  base::Vector<const ValueType> br_types, bool emit_end = true)
425  : gen_(gen), emit_end_(emit_end) {
426  gen->blocks_.emplace_back(br_types.begin(), br_types.end());
427  gen->builder_->EmitByte(block_type);
428 
429  if (param_types.size() == 0 && result_types.size() == 0) {
430  gen->builder_->EmitValueType(kWasmVoid);
431  return;
432  }
433  if (param_types.size() == 0 && result_types.size() == 1) {
434  gen->builder_->EmitValueType(result_types[0]);
435  return;
436  }
437  // Multi-value block.
438  Zone* zone = gen->builder_->builder()->zone();
439  FunctionSig::Builder builder(zone, result_types.size(),
440  param_types.size());
441  for (auto& type : param_types) {
442  DCHECK_NE(type, kWasmVoid);
443  builder.AddParam(type);
444  }
445  for (auto& type : result_types) {
446  DCHECK_NE(type, kWasmVoid);
447  builder.AddReturn(type);
448  }
449  FunctionSig* sig = builder.Get();
450  const bool is_final = true;
451  ModuleTypeIndex sig_id =
452  gen->builder_->builder()->AddSignature(sig, is_final);
453  gen->builder_->EmitI32V(sig_id);
454  }
455 
456  ~BlockScope() {
457  if (emit_end_) gen_->builder_->Emit(kExprEnd);
458  gen_->blocks_.pop_back();
459  }
460 
461  private:
462  BodyGen* const gen_;
463  bool emit_end_;
464  };
465 
466  void block(base::Vector<const ValueType> param_types,
467  base::Vector<const ValueType> return_types, DataRange* data) {
468  BlockScope block_scope(this, kExprBlock, param_types, return_types,
469  return_types);
470  ConsumeAndGenerate(param_types, return_types, data);
471  }
472 
473  template <ValueKind T>
474  void block(DataRange* data) {
475  if constexpr (T == kVoid) {
476  block({}, {}, data);
477  } else {
478  block({}, base::VectorOf({ValueType::Primitive(T)}), data);
479  }
480  }
481 
482  void loop(base::Vector<const ValueType> param_types,
483  base::Vector<const ValueType> return_types, DataRange* data) {
484  BlockScope block_scope(this, kExprLoop, param_types, return_types,
485  param_types);
486  ConsumeAndGenerate(param_types, return_types, data);
487  }
488 
489  template <ValueKind T>
490  void loop(DataRange* data) {
491  if constexpr (T == kVoid) {
492  loop({}, {}, data);
493  } else {
494  loop({}, base::VectorOf({ValueType::Primitive(T)}), data);
495  }
496  }
497 
498  void finite_loop(base::Vector<const ValueType> param_types,
499  base::Vector<const ValueType> return_types,
500  DataRange* data) {
501  // int counter = `kLoopConstant`;
502  int kLoopConstant = data->get<uint8_t>() % 8 + 1;
503  uint32_t counter = builder_->AddLocal(kWasmI32);
504  builder_->EmitI32Const(kLoopConstant);
505  builder_->EmitSetLocal(counter);
506 
507  // begin loop {
508  BlockScope loop_scope(this, kExprLoop, param_types, return_types,
509  param_types);
510  // Consume the parameters:
511  // Resetting locals in each iteration can create interesting loop-phis.
512  // TODO(evih): Iterate through existing locals and try to reuse them instead
513  // of creating new locals.
514  for (auto it = param_types.rbegin(); it != param_types.rend(); it++) {
515  uint32_t local = builder_->AddLocal(*it);
516  builder_->EmitSetLocal(local);
517  }
518 
519  // Loop body.
520  Generate(kWasmVoid, data);
521 
522  // Decrement the counter.
523  builder_->EmitGetLocal(counter);
524  builder_->EmitI32Const(1);
525  builder_->Emit(kExprI32Sub);
526  builder_->EmitTeeLocal(counter);
527 
528  // If there is another iteration, generate new parameters for the loop and
529  // go to the beginning of the loop.
530  {
531  BlockScope if_scope(this, kExprIf, {}, {}, {});
532  Generate(param_types, data);
533  builder_->EmitWithI32V(kExprBr, 1);
534  }
535 
536  // Otherwise, generate the return types.
537  Generate(return_types, data);
538  // } end loop
539  }
540 
541  template <ValueKind T>
542  void finite_loop(DataRange* data) {
543  if constexpr (T == kVoid) {
544  finite_loop({}, {}, data);
545  } else {
546  finite_loop({}, base::VectorOf({ValueType::Primitive(T)}), data);
547  }
548  }
549 
550  enum IfType { kIf, kIfElse };
551 
552  void if_(base::Vector<const ValueType> param_types,
553  base::Vector<const ValueType> return_types, IfType type,
554  DataRange* data) {
555  // One-armed "if" are only valid if the input and output types are the same.
556  DCHECK_IMPLIES(type == kIf, param_types == return_types);
557  Generate(kWasmI32, data);
558  BlockScope block_scope(this, kExprIf, param_types, return_types,
559  return_types);
560  ConsumeAndGenerate(param_types, return_types, data);
561  if (type == kIfElse) {
562  builder_->Emit(kExprElse);
563  ConsumeAndGenerate(param_types, return_types, data);
564  }
565  }
566 
567  template <ValueKind T, IfType type>
568  void if_(DataRange* data) {
569  static_assert(T == kVoid || type == kIfElse,
570  "if without else cannot produce a value");
571  if_({},
572  T == kVoid ? base::Vector<ValueType>{}
573  : base::VectorOf({ValueType::Primitive(T)}),
574  type, data);
575  }
576 
577  void try_block_helper(ValueType return_type, DataRange* data) {
578  bool has_catch_all = data->get<bool>();
579  uint8_t num_catch =
580  data->get<uint8_t>() % (builder_->builder()->NumTags() + 1);
581  bool is_delegate = num_catch == 0 && !has_catch_all && data->get<bool>();
582  // Allow one more target than there are enclosing try blocks, for delegating
583  // to the caller.
584 
585  base::Vector<const ValueType> return_type_vec =
586  return_type.kind() == kVoid ? base::Vector<ValueType>{}
587  : base::VectorOf(&return_type, 1);
588  BlockScope block_scope(this, kExprTry, {}, return_type_vec, return_type_vec,
589  !is_delegate);
590  int control_depth = static_cast<int>(blocks_.size()) - 1;
591  Generate(return_type, data);
592  catch_blocks_.push_back(control_depth);
593  for (int i = 0; i < num_catch; ++i) {
594  const FunctionSig* exception_type = builder_->builder()->GetTagType(i);
595  builder_->EmitWithU32V(kExprCatch, i);
596  ConsumeAndGenerate(exception_type->parameters(), return_type_vec, data);
597  }
598  if (has_catch_all) {
599  builder_->Emit(kExprCatchAll);
600  Generate(return_type, data);
601  }
602  if (is_delegate) {
603  // The delegate target depth does not include the current try block,
604  // because 'delegate' closes this scope. However it is still in the
605  // {blocks_} list, so remove one to get the correct size.
606  int delegate_depth = data->get<uint8_t>() % (blocks_.size() - 1);
607  builder_->EmitWithU32V(kExprDelegate, delegate_depth);
608  }
609  catch_blocks_.pop_back();
610  }
611 
612  template <ValueKind T>
613  void try_block(DataRange* data) {
614  try_block_helper(ValueType::Primitive(T), data);
615  }
616 
617  struct CatchCase {
618  int tag_index;
619  CatchKind kind;
620  };
621 
622  // Generates the i-th nested block for the try-table, and recursively generate
623  // the blocks inside it.
624  void try_table_rec(base::Vector<const ValueType> param_types,
625  base::Vector<const ValueType> return_types,
626  base::Vector<CatchCase> catch_cases, size_t i,
627  DataRange* data) {
628  DCHECK(v8_flags.experimental_wasm_exnref);
629  if (i == catch_cases.size()) {
630  // Base case: emit the try-table itself.
631  builder_->Emit(kExprTryTable);
632  blocks_.emplace_back(return_types.begin(), return_types.end());
633  const bool is_final = true;
634  ModuleTypeIndex try_sig_index = builder_->builder()->AddSignature(
635  CreateSignature(builder_->builder()->zone(), param_types,
636  return_types),
637  is_final);
638  builder_->EmitI32V(try_sig_index);
639  builder_->EmitU32V(static_cast<uint32_t>(catch_cases.size()));
640  for (size_t j = 0; j < catch_cases.size(); ++j) {
641  builder_->EmitByte(catch_cases[j].kind);
642  if (catch_cases[j].kind == kCatch || catch_cases[j].kind == kCatchRef) {
643  builder_->EmitByte(catch_cases[j].tag_index);
644  }
645  builder_->EmitByte(catch_cases.size() - j - 1);
646  }
647  ConsumeAndGenerate(param_types, return_types, data);
648  builder_->Emit(kExprEnd);
649  blocks_.pop_back();
650  builder_->EmitWithI32V(kExprBr, static_cast<int32_t>(catch_cases.size()));
651  return;
652  }
653 
654  // Enter the i-th nested block. The signature of the block is built as
655  // follows:
656  // - The input types are the same for each block, the operands are forwarded
657  // as-is to the inner try-table.
658  // - The output types can be empty, or contain the tag types and/or an
659  // exnref depending on the catch kind
660  const FunctionSig* type =
661  builder_->builder()->GetTagType(catch_cases[i].tag_index);
662  int has_tag =
663  catch_cases[i].kind == kCatchRef || catch_cases[i].kind == kCatch;
664  int has_ref =
665  catch_cases[i].kind == kCatchAllRef || catch_cases[i].kind == kCatchRef;
666  size_t return_count =
667  (has_tag ? type->parameter_count() : 0) + (has_ref ? 1 : 0);
668  auto block_returns =
669  builder_->builder()->zone()->AllocateVector<ValueType>(return_count);
670  if (has_tag) {
671  std::copy_n(type->parameters().begin(), type->parameter_count(),
672  block_returns.begin());
673  }
674  if (has_ref) block_returns.last() = kWasmExnRef;
675  {
676  BlockScope block(this, kExprBlock, param_types, block_returns,
677  block_returns);
678  try_table_rec(param_types, return_types, catch_cases, i + 1, data);
679  }
680  // Catch label. Consume the unpacked values and exnref (if any), produce
681  // values that match the outer scope, and branch to it.
682  ConsumeAndGenerate(block_returns, return_types, data);
683  builder_->EmitWithU32V(kExprBr, static_cast<uint32_t>(i));
684  }
685 
686  void try_table_block_helper(base::Vector<const ValueType> param_types,
687  base::Vector<const ValueType> return_types,
688  DataRange* data) {
689  uint8_t num_catch = data->get<uint8_t>() % kMaxCatchCases;
690  auto catch_cases =
691  builder_->builder()->zone()->AllocateVector<CatchCase>(num_catch);
692  for (int i = 0; i < num_catch; ++i) {
693  catch_cases[i].tag_index =
694  data->get<uint8_t>() % builder_->builder()->NumTags();
695  catch_cases[i].kind =
696  static_cast<CatchKind>(data->get<uint8_t>() % (kLastCatchKind + 1));
697  }
698 
699  BlockScope block_scope(this, kExprBlock, param_types, return_types,
700  return_types);
701  try_table_rec(param_types, return_types, catch_cases, 0, data);
702  }
703 
704  template <ValueKind T>
705  void try_table_block(DataRange* data) {
706  ValueType return_types_arr[1] = {ValueType::Primitive(T)};
707  auto return_types = base::VectorOf(return_types_arr, T == kVoid ? 0 : 1);
708  if (!v8_flags.experimental_wasm_exnref) {
709  // Can't generate a try_table block. Just generate something else.
710  any_block({}, return_types, data);
711  return;
712  }
713  try_table_block_helper({}, return_types, data);
714  }
715 
716  void any_block(base::Vector<const ValueType> param_types,
717  base::Vector<const ValueType> return_types, DataRange* data) {
718  uint8_t available_cases = v8_flags.experimental_wasm_exnref ? 6 : 5;
719  uint8_t block_type = data->get<uint8_t>() % available_cases;
720  switch (block_type) {
721  case 0:
722  block(param_types, return_types, data);
723  return;
724  case 1:
725  loop(param_types, return_types, data);
726  return;
727  case 2:
728  finite_loop(param_types, return_types, data);
729  return;
730  case 3:
731  if (param_types == return_types) {
732  if_({}, {}, kIf, data);
733  return;
734  }
735  [[fallthrough]];
736  case 4:
737  if_(param_types, return_types, kIfElse, data);
738  return;
739  case 5:
740  try_table_block_helper(param_types, return_types, data);
741  return;
742  }
743  }
744 
745  void br(DataRange* data) {
746  // There is always at least the block representing the function body.
747  DCHECK(!blocks_.empty());
748  const uint32_t target_block = data->get<uint8_t>() % blocks_.size();
749  const auto break_types = base::VectorOf(blocks_[target_block]);
750 
751  Generate(break_types, data);
752  builder_->EmitWithI32V(
753  kExprBr, static_cast<uint32_t>(blocks_.size()) - 1 - target_block);
754  }
755 
756  template <ValueKind wanted_kind>
757  void br_if(DataRange* data) {
758  // There is always at least the block representing the function body.
759  DCHECK(!blocks_.empty());
760  const uint32_t target_block = data->get<uint8_t>() % blocks_.size();
761  const auto break_types = base::VectorOf(blocks_[target_block]);
762 
763  Generate(break_types, data);
764  Generate(kWasmI32, data);
765  builder_->EmitWithI32V(
766  kExprBrIf, static_cast<uint32_t>(blocks_.size()) - 1 - target_block);
767  ConsumeAndGenerate(
768  break_types,
769  wanted_kind == kVoid
770  ? base::Vector<ValueType>{}
771  : base::VectorOf({ValueType::Primitive(wanted_kind)}),
772  data);
773  }
774 
775  template <ValueKind wanted_kind>
776  void br_on_null(DataRange* data) {
777  DCHECK(!blocks_.empty());
778  const uint32_t target_block = data->get<uint8_t>() % blocks_.size();
779  const auto break_types = base::VectorOf(blocks_[target_block]);
780  Generate(break_types, data);
781  GenerateRef(data);
782  builder_->EmitWithI32V(
783  kExprBrOnNull,
784  static_cast<uint32_t>(blocks_.size()) - 1 - target_block);
785  builder_->Emit(kExprDrop);
786  ConsumeAndGenerate(
787  break_types,
788  wanted_kind == kVoid
789  ? base::Vector<ValueType>{}
790  : base::VectorOf({ValueType::Primitive(wanted_kind)}),
791  data);
792  }
793 
794  template <ValueKind wanted_kind>
795  void br_on_non_null(DataRange* data) {
796  DCHECK(!blocks_.empty());
797  const uint32_t target_block = data->get<uint8_t>() % blocks_.size();
798  const auto break_types = base::VectorOf(blocks_[target_block]);
799  if (break_types.empty() ||
800  !break_types[break_types.size() - 1].is_reference()) {
801  // Invalid break_types for br_on_non_null.
802  Generate<wanted_kind>(data);
803  return;
804  }
805  Generate(break_types, data);
806  builder_->EmitWithI32V(
807  kExprBrOnNonNull,
808  static_cast<uint32_t>(blocks_.size()) - 1 - target_block);
809  ConsumeAndGenerate(
810  break_types.SubVector(0, break_types.size() - 1),
811  wanted_kind == kVoid
812  ? base::Vector<ValueType>{}
813  : base::VectorOf({ValueType::Primitive(wanted_kind)}),
814  data);
815  }
816 
817  void br_table(ValueType result_type, DataRange* data) {
818  const uint8_t block_count = 1 + data->get<uint8_t>() % 8;
819  // Generate the block entries.
820  uint16_t entry_bits =
821  block_count > 4 ? data->get<uint16_t>() : data->get<uint8_t>();
822  for (size_t i = 0; i < block_count; ++i) {
823  builder_->Emit(kExprBlock);
824  builder_->EmitValueType(result_type);
825  blocks_.emplace_back();
826  if (result_type != kWasmVoid) {
827  blocks_.back().push_back(result_type);
828  }
829  // There can be additional instructions in each block.
830  // Only generate it with a 25% chance as it's otherwise quite unlikely to
831  // have enough random bytes left for the br_table instruction.
832  if ((entry_bits & 3) == 3) {
833  Generate(kWasmVoid, data);
834  }
835  entry_bits >>= 2;
836  }
837  // Generate the br_table.
838  Generate(result_type, data);
839  Generate(kWasmI32, data);
840  builder_->Emit(kExprBrTable);
841  uint32_t entry_count = 1 + data->get<uint8_t>() % 8;
842  builder_->EmitU32V(entry_count);
843  for (size_t i = 0; i < entry_count + 1; ++i) {
844  builder_->EmitU32V(data->get<uint8_t>() % block_count);
845  }
846  // Generate the block ends.
847  uint8_t exit_bits = result_type == kWasmVoid ? 0 : data->get<uint8_t>();
848  for (size_t i = 0; i < block_count; ++i) {
849  if (exit_bits & 1) {
850  // Drop and generate new value.
851  builder_->Emit(kExprDrop);
852  Generate(result_type, data);
853  }
854  exit_bits >>= 1;
855  builder_->Emit(kExprEnd);
856  blocks_.pop_back();
857  }
858  }
859 
860  template <ValueKind wanted_kind>
861  void br_table(DataRange* data) {
862  br_table(
863  wanted_kind == kVoid ? kWasmVoid : ValueType::Primitive(wanted_kind),
864  data);
865  }
866 
867  void return_op(DataRange* data) {
868  auto returns = builder_->signature()->returns();
869  Generate(returns, data);
870  builder_->Emit(kExprReturn);
871  }
872 
873  constexpr static uint8_t max_alignment(WasmOpcode memop) {
874  switch (memop) {
875  case kExprS128LoadMem:
876  case kExprS128StoreMem:
877  return 4;
878  case kExprI64LoadMem:
879  case kExprF64LoadMem:
880  case kExprI64StoreMem:
881  case kExprF64StoreMem:
882  case kExprI64AtomicStore:
883  case kExprI64AtomicLoad:
884  case kExprI64AtomicAdd:
885  case kExprI64AtomicSub:
886  case kExprI64AtomicAnd:
887  case kExprI64AtomicOr:
888  case kExprI64AtomicXor:
889  case kExprI64AtomicExchange:
890  case kExprI64AtomicCompareExchange:
891  case kExprS128Load8x8S:
892  case kExprS128Load8x8U:
893  case kExprS128Load16x4S:
894  case kExprS128Load16x4U:
895  case kExprS128Load32x2S:
896  case kExprS128Load32x2U:
897  case kExprS128Load64Splat:
898  case kExprS128Load64Zero:
899  return 3;
900  case kExprI32LoadMem:
901  case kExprI64LoadMem32S:
902  case kExprI64LoadMem32U:
903  case kExprF32LoadMem:
904  case kExprI32StoreMem:
905  case kExprI64StoreMem32:
906  case kExprF32StoreMem:
907  case kExprI32AtomicStore:
908  case kExprI64AtomicStore32U:
909  case kExprI32AtomicLoad:
910  case kExprI64AtomicLoad32U:
911  case kExprI32AtomicAdd:
912  case kExprI32AtomicSub:
913  case kExprI32AtomicAnd:
914  case kExprI32AtomicOr:
915  case kExprI32AtomicXor:
916  case kExprI32AtomicExchange:
917  case kExprI32AtomicCompareExchange:
918  case kExprI64AtomicAdd32U:
919  case kExprI64AtomicSub32U:
920  case kExprI64AtomicAnd32U:
921  case kExprI64AtomicOr32U:
922  case kExprI64AtomicXor32U:
923  case kExprI64AtomicExchange32U:
924  case kExprI64AtomicCompareExchange32U:
925  case kExprS128Load32Splat:
926  case kExprS128Load32Zero:
927  return 2;
928  case kExprI32LoadMem16S:
929  case kExprI32LoadMem16U:
930  case kExprI64LoadMem16S:
931  case kExprI64LoadMem16U:
932  case kExprI32StoreMem16:
933  case kExprI64StoreMem16:
934  case kExprI32AtomicStore16U:
935  case kExprI64AtomicStore16U:
936  case kExprI32AtomicLoad16U:
937  case kExprI64AtomicLoad16U:
938  case kExprI32AtomicAdd16U:
939  case kExprI32AtomicSub16U:
940  case kExprI32AtomicAnd16U:
941  case kExprI32AtomicOr16U:
942  case kExprI32AtomicXor16U:
943  case kExprI32AtomicExchange16U:
944  case kExprI32AtomicCompareExchange16U:
945  case kExprI64AtomicAdd16U:
946  case kExprI64AtomicSub16U:
947  case kExprI64AtomicAnd16U:
948  case kExprI64AtomicOr16U:
949  case kExprI64AtomicXor16U:
950  case kExprI64AtomicExchange16U:
951  case kExprI64AtomicCompareExchange16U:
952  case kExprS128Load16Splat:
953  return 1;
954  case kExprI32LoadMem8S:
955  case kExprI32LoadMem8U:
956  case kExprI64LoadMem8S:
957  case kExprI64LoadMem8U:
958  case kExprI32StoreMem8:
959  case kExprI64StoreMem8:
960  case kExprI32AtomicStore8U:
961  case kExprI64AtomicStore8U:
962  case kExprI32AtomicLoad8U:
963  case kExprI64AtomicLoad8U:
964  case kExprI32AtomicAdd8U:
965  case kExprI32AtomicSub8U:
966  case kExprI32AtomicAnd8U:
967  case kExprI32AtomicOr8U:
968  case kExprI32AtomicXor8U:
969  case kExprI32AtomicExchange8U:
970  case kExprI32AtomicCompareExchange8U:
971  case kExprI64AtomicAdd8U:
972  case kExprI64AtomicSub8U:
973  case kExprI64AtomicAnd8U:
974  case kExprI64AtomicOr8U:
975  case kExprI64AtomicXor8U:
976  case kExprI64AtomicExchange8U:
977  case kExprI64AtomicCompareExchange8U:
978  case kExprS128Load8Splat:
979  return 0;
980  default:
981  return 0;
982  }
983  }
984 
985  template <WasmOpcode memory_op, ValueKind... arg_kinds>
986  void memop(DataRange* data) {
987  // Atomic operations need to be aligned exactly to their max alignment.
988  const bool is_atomic = memory_op >> 8 == kAtomicPrefix;
989  const uint8_t align = is_atomic ? max_alignment(memory_op)
990  : data->getPseudoRandom<uint8_t>() %
991  (max_alignment(memory_op) + 1);
992 
993  uint8_t memory_index =
994  data->get<uint8_t>() % builder_->builder()->NumMemories();
995 
996  uint64_t offset = data->get<uint16_t>();
997  // With a 1/256 chance generate potentially very large offsets.
998  if ((offset & 0xff) == 0xff) {
999  offset = builder_->builder()->IsMemory64(memory_index)
1000  ? data->getPseudoRandom<uint64_t>() & 0x1ffffffff
1001  : data->getPseudoRandom<uint32_t>();
1002  }
1003 
1004  // Generate the index and the arguments, if any.
1005  builder_->builder()->IsMemory64(memory_index)
1006  ? Generate<kI64, arg_kinds...>(data)
1007  : Generate<kI32, arg_kinds...>(data);
1008 
1009  // Format of the instruction (supports multi-memory):
1010  // memory_op (align | 0x40) memory_index offset
1011  if (WasmOpcodes::IsPrefixOpcode(static_cast<WasmOpcode>(memory_op >> 8))) {
1012  DCHECK(memory_op >> 8 == kAtomicPrefix || memory_op >> 8 == kSimdPrefix);
1013  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(memory_op);
1014  } else {
1015  builder_->Emit(memory_op);
1016  }
1017  builder_->EmitU32V(align | 0x40);
1018  builder_->EmitU32V(memory_index);
1019  builder_->EmitU64V(offset);
1020  }
1021 
1022  template <WasmOpcode Op, ValueKind... Args>
1023  void op_with_prefix(DataRange* data) {
1024  Generate<Args...>(data);
1025  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(Op);
1026  }
1027 
1028  void simd_const(DataRange* data) {
1029  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(kExprS128Const);
1030  for (int i = 0; i < kSimd128Size; i++) {
1031  builder_->EmitByte(data->getPseudoRandom<uint8_t>());
1032  }
1033  }
1034 
1035  template <WasmOpcode Op, int lanes, ValueKind... Args>
1036  void simd_lane_op(DataRange* data) {
1037  Generate<Args...>(data);
1038  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(Op);
1039  builder_->EmitByte(data->get<uint8_t>() % lanes);
1040  }
1041 
1042  template <WasmOpcode Op, int lanes, ValueKind... Args>
1043  void simd_lane_memop(DataRange* data) {
1044  // Simd load/store instructions that have a lane immediate.
1045  memop<Op, Args...>(data);
1046  builder_->EmitByte(data->get<uint8_t>() % lanes);
1047  }

1049  void simd_shuffle(DataRange* data) {
1050  Generate<kS128, kS128>(data);
1051  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(kExprI8x16Shuffle);
1052  for (int i = 0; i < kSimd128Size; i++) {
1053  builder_->EmitByte(static_cast<uint8_t>(data->get<uint8_t>() % 32));
1054  }
1055  }

1058  Generate(
1059  GetValueType(options_, data,
1060  static_cast<uint32_t>(functions_.size() + structs_.size() +
1061  arrays_.size())),
1062  data);
1063  builder_->Emit(kExprDrop);

1066  enum CallKind { kCallDirect, kCallIndirect, kCallRef };
1067 
1068  template <ValueKind wanted_kind>
1069  void call(DataRange* data) {
1070  call(data, ValueType::Primitive(wanted_kind), kCallDirect);
1071  }
1072 
1073  template <ValueKind wanted_kind>
1074  void call_indirect(DataRange* data) {
1075  call(data, ValueType::Primitive(wanted_kind), kCallIndirect);
1076  }
1077 
1078  template <ValueKind wanted_kind>
1079  void call_ref(DataRange* data) {
1080  call(data, ValueType::Primitive(wanted_kind), kCallRef);

1082 
1083  void Convert(ValueType src, ValueType dst) {
1084  auto idx = [](ValueType t) -> int {
1085  switch (t.kind()) {
1086  case kI32:
1087  return 0;
1088  case kI64:
1089  return 1;
1090  case kF32:
1091  return 2;
1092  case kF64:
1093  return 3;
1094  default:
1095  UNREACHABLE();
1096  }
1097  };
1098  static constexpr WasmOpcode kConvertOpcodes[] = {
1099  // {i32, i64, f32, f64} -> i32
1100  kExprNop, kExprI32ConvertI64, kExprI32SConvertF32, kExprI32SConvertF64,
1101  // {i32, i64, f32, f64} -> i64
1102  kExprI64SConvertI32, kExprNop, kExprI64SConvertF32, kExprI64SConvertF64,
1103  // {i32, i64, f32, f64} -> f32
1104  kExprF32SConvertI32, kExprF32SConvertI64, kExprNop, kExprF32ConvertF64,
1105  // {i32, i64, f32, f64} -> f64
1106  kExprF64SConvertI32, kExprF64SConvertI64, kExprF64ConvertF32, kExprNop};
1107  int arr_idx = idx(dst) << 2 | idx(src);
1108  builder_->Emit(kConvertOpcodes[arr_idx]);
1109  }
1110 
1111  int choose_function_table_index(DataRange* data) {
1112  int table_count = builder_->builder()->NumTables();
1113  int start = data->get<uint8_t>() % table_count;
1114  for (int i = 0; i < table_count; ++i) {
1115  int index = (start + i) % table_count;
1116  if (builder_->builder()->GetTableType(index).is_reference_to(
1117  HeapType::kFunc)) {
1118  return index;
1119  }
1120  }
1121  FATAL("No funcref table found; table index 0 is expected to be funcref");
1122  }
1123 
1124  void call(DataRange* data, ValueType wanted_kind, CallKind call_kind) {
1125  uint8_t random_byte = data->get<uint8_t>();
1126  int func_index = random_byte % functions_.size();
1127  ModuleTypeIndex sig_index = functions_[func_index];
1128  const FunctionSig* sig = builder_->builder()->GetSignature(sig_index);
1129  // Generate arguments.
1130  for (size_t i = 0; i < sig->parameter_count(); ++i) {
1131  Generate(sig->GetParam(i), data);
1132  }
1133  // Emit call.
1134  // If the return types of the callee happen to match the return types of the
1135  // caller, generate a tail call.
1136  bool use_return_call = random_byte > 127;
1137  if (use_return_call &&
1138  std::equal(sig->returns().begin(), sig->returns().end(),
1139  builder_->signature()->returns().begin(),
1140  builder_->signature()->returns().end())) {
1141  if (call_kind == kCallDirect) {
1142  builder_->EmitWithU32V(kExprReturnCall,
1143  NumImportedFunctions() + func_index);
1144  } else if (call_kind == kCallIndirect) {
1145  // This will not trap because table[func_index] always contains function
1146  // func_index.
1147  uint32_t table_index = choose_function_table_index(data);
1148  builder_->builder()->IsTable64(table_index)
1149  ? builder_->EmitI64Const(func_index)
1150  : builder_->EmitI32Const(func_index);
1151  builder_->EmitWithU32V(kExprReturnCallIndirect, sig_index);
1152  builder_->EmitByte(table_index);
1153  } else {
1154  GenerateRef(
1155  HeapType::Index(sig_index, kNotShared, RefTypeKind::kFunction),
1156  data);
1157  builder_->EmitWithU32V(kExprReturnCallRef, sig_index);
1158  }
1159  return;
1160  } else {
1161  if (call_kind == kCallDirect) {
1162  builder_->EmitWithU32V(kExprCallFunction,
1163  NumImportedFunctions() + func_index);
1164  } else if (call_kind == kCallIndirect) {
1165  // This will not trap because table[func_index] always contains function
1166  // func_index.
1167  uint32_t table_index = choose_function_table_index(data);
1168  builder_->builder()->IsTable64(table_index)
1169  ? builder_->EmitI64Const(func_index)
1170  : builder_->EmitI32Const(func_index);
1171  builder_->EmitWithU32V(kExprCallIndirect, sig_index);
1172  builder_->EmitByte(table_index);
1173  } else {
1174  GenerateRef(
1175  HeapType::Index(sig_index, kNotShared, RefTypeKind::kFunction),
1176  data);
1177  builder_->EmitWithU32V(kExprCallRef, sig_index);
1178  }
1179  }
1180  if (sig->return_count() == 0 && wanted_kind != kWasmVoid) {
1181  // The call did not generate a value. Thus just generate it here.
1182  Generate(wanted_kind, data);
1183  return;
1184  }
1185  if (wanted_kind == kWasmVoid) {
1186  // The call did generate values, but we did not want one.
1187  for (size_t i = 0; i < sig->return_count(); ++i) {
1188  builder_->Emit(kExprDrop);
1189  }
1190  return;
1191  }
1192  auto wanted_types =
1193  base::VectorOf(&wanted_kind, wanted_kind == kWasmVoid ? 0 : 1);
1194  ConsumeAndGenerate(sig->returns(), wanted_types, data);
1195  }
1196 
1197  struct Var {
1198  uint32_t index;
1199  ValueType type = kWasmVoid;
1200  Var() = default;
1201  Var(uint32_t index, ValueType type) : index(index), type(type) {}
1202  bool is_valid() const { return type != kWasmVoid; }
1203  };
1204 
1205  ValueType AsNullable(ValueType original) {
1206  if (!original.is_ref()) return original;
1207  return original.AsNullable();
1208  }
1209 
1210  Var GetRandomLocal(DataRange* data, ValueType type = kWasmTop) {
1211  const size_t locals_count = all_locals_count();
1212  if (locals_count == 0) return {};
1213  uint32_t start_index = data->get<uint8_t>() % locals_count;
1214  uint32_t index = start_index;
1215  // TODO(14034): Ideally we would check for subtyping here over type
1216  // equality, but we don't have a module.
1217  while (type != kWasmTop && local_type(index) != type &&
1218  AsNullable(local_type(index)) != type) {
1219  index = (index + 1) % locals_count;
1220  if (index == start_index) return {};
1221  }
1222  return {index, local_type(index)};
1223  }
1224 
1225  constexpr static bool is_convertible_kind(ValueKind kind) {
1226  return kind == kI32 || kind == kI64 || kind == kF32 || kind == kF64;
1227  }
1228 
1229  template <ValueKind wanted_kind>
1230  void local_op(DataRange* data, WasmOpcode opcode) {
1231  static_assert(wanted_kind == kVoid || is_convertible_kind(wanted_kind));
1232  Var local = GetRandomLocal(data);
1233  // If there are no locals and no parameters, just generate any value (if a
1234  // value is needed), or do nothing.
1235  if (!local.is_valid() || !is_convertible_kind(local.type.kind())) {
1236  if (wanted_kind == kVoid) return;
1237  return Generate<wanted_kind>(data);
1238  }
1239 
1240  if (opcode != kExprLocalGet) Generate(local.type, data);
1241  builder_->EmitWithU32V(opcode, local.index);
1242  if (wanted_kind != kVoid && local.type.kind() != wanted_kind) {
1243  Convert(local.type, ValueType::Primitive(wanted_kind));
1244  }
1245  }
1246 
1247  template <ValueKind wanted_kind>
1248  void get_local(DataRange* data) {
1249  static_assert(wanted_kind != kVoid, "illegal type");
1250  local_op<wanted_kind>(data, kExprLocalGet);
1251  }
1252 
1253  void set_local(DataRange* data) { local_op<kVoid>(data, kExprLocalSet); }
1254 
1255  template <ValueKind wanted_kind>
1256  void tee_local(DataRange* data) {
1257  local_op<wanted_kind>(data, kExprLocalTee);
1258  }
1259 
1260  // Shifts the assigned values of some locals towards the start_local.
1261  // Assuming 4 locals with index 0-3 of the same type and start_local with
1262  // index 0, this emits e.g.:
1263  // local.set 0 (local.get 1)
1264  // local.set 1 (local.get 2)
1265  // local.set 2 (local.get 3)
1266  // If this is executed in a loop, the value in local 3 will eventually end up
1267  // in local 0, but only after multiple iterations of the loop.
1268  void shift_locals_to(DataRange* data, Var start_local) {
1269  const uint32_t max_shift = data->get<uint8_t>() % 8 + 2;
1270  const auto [start_index, type] = start_local;
1271  const size_t locals_count = all_locals_count();
1272  uint32_t previous_index = start_index;
1273  uint32_t index = start_index;
1274  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < max_shift; ++i) {
1275  do {
1276  index = (index + 1) % locals_count;
1277  } while (local_type(index) != type);
1278  // Never emit more than one shift over all same-typed locals.
1279  // (In many cases we might end up with only one local with the same type.)
1280  if (index == start_index) break;
1281  builder_->EmitGetLocal(index);
1282  builder_->EmitSetLocal(previous_index);
1283  previous_index = index;
1284  }
1285  }
1286 
1287  void shift_locals(DataRange* data) {
1288  const Var local = GetRandomLocal(data);
1289  if (local.type == kWasmVoid ||
1290  (local.type.is_non_nullable() && !locals_initialized_)) {
1291  return;
1292  }
1293  shift_locals_to(data, local);
1294  }
1295 
1296  template <size_t num_bytes>
1297  void i32_const(DataRange* data) {
1298  builder_->EmitI32Const(data->getPseudoRandom<int32_t, num_bytes>());
1299  }
1300 
1301  template <size_t num_bytes>
1302  void i64_const(DataRange* data) {
1303  builder_->EmitI64Const(data->getPseudoRandom<int64_t, num_bytes>());
1304  }

1306  Var GetRandomGlobal(DataRange* data, bool ensure_mutable) {
1307  uint32_t index;
1308  if (ensure_mutable) {
1309  if (mutable_globals_.empty()) return {};
1310  index = mutable_globals_[data->get<uint8_t>() % mutable_globals_.size()];
1311  } else {
1312  if (globals_.empty()) return {};
1313  index = data->get<uint8_t>() % globals_.size();
1314  }
1315  ValueType type = globals_[index];
1316  return {index, type};
1317  }
1318 
1319  template <ValueKind wanted_kind>
1320  void global_op(DataRange* data) {
1321  static_assert(wanted_kind == kVoid || is_convertible_kind(wanted_kind));
1322  constexpr bool is_set = wanted_kind == kVoid;
1323  Var global = GetRandomGlobal(data, is_set);
1324  // If there are no globals, just generate any value (if a value is needed),
1325  // or do nothing.
1326  if (!global.is_valid() || !is_convertible_kind(global.type.kind())) {
1327  if (wanted_kind == kVoid) return;
1328  return Generate<wanted_kind>(data);
1329  }
1330 
1331  if (is_set) Generate(global.type, data);
1332  builder_->EmitWithU32V(is_set ? kExprGlobalSet : kExprGlobalGet,
1333  global.index);
1334  if (!is_set && global.type.kind() != wanted_kind) {
1335  Convert(global.type, ValueType::Primitive(wanted_kind));
1336  }
1337  }
1338 
1339  template <ValueKind wanted_kind>
1340  void get_global(DataRange* data) {
1341  static_assert(wanted_kind != kVoid, "illegal type");
1342  global_op<wanted_kind>(data);
1343  }

1345  template <ValueKind select_kind>
1346  void select_with_type(DataRange* data) {
1347  static_assert(select_kind != kVoid, "illegal kind for select");
1348  Generate<select_kind, select_kind, kI32>(data);
1349  // num_types is always 1.
1350  uint8_t num_types = 1;
1351  builder_->EmitWithU8U8(kExprSelectWithType, num_types,
1352  ValueType::Primitive(select_kind).value_type_code());
1353  }

1355  void set_global(DataRange* data) { global_op<kVoid>(data); }

1357  void throw_or_rethrow(DataRange* data) {
1358  bool rethrow = data->get<bool>();
1359  if (rethrow && !catch_blocks_.empty()) {
1360  int control_depth = static_cast<int>(blocks_.size() - 1);
1361  int catch_index =
1362  data->get<uint8_t>() % static_cast<int>(catch_blocks_.size());
1363  builder_->EmitWithU32V(kExprRethrow,
1364  control_depth - catch_blocks_[catch_index]);
1365  } else {
1366  int tag = data->get<uint8_t>() % builder_->builder()->NumTags();
1367  const FunctionSig* exception_sig = builder_->builder()->GetTagType(tag);
1368  Generate(exception_sig->parameters(), data);
1369  builder_->EmitWithU32V(kExprThrow, tag);
1370  }
1371  }

1376  }

1378  void memory_size(DataRange* data) {
1379  uint8_t memory_index =
1380  data->get<uint8_t>() % builder_->builder()->NumMemories();
1381 
1382  builder_->EmitWithU8(kExprMemorySize, memory_index);
1383  // The `memory_size` returns an I32. However, `kExprMemorySize` for memory64
1384  // returns an I64, so we should convert it.
1385  if (builder_->builder()->IsMemory64(memory_index)) {
1386  builder_->Emit(kExprI32ConvertI64);
1387  }
1388  }

1390  void grow_memory(DataRange* data) {
1391  uint8_t memory_index =
1392  data->get<uint8_t>() % builder_->builder()->NumMemories();
1393 
1394  // Generate the index and the arguments, if any.
1395  builder_->builder()->IsMemory64(memory_index) ? Generate<kI64>(data)
1396  : Generate<kI32>(data);
1397  builder_->EmitWithU8(kExprMemoryGrow, memory_index);
1398  // The `grow_memory` returns an I32. However, `kExprMemoryGrow` for memory64
1399  // returns an I64, so we should convert it.
1400  if (builder_->builder()->IsMemory64(memory_index)) {
1401  builder_->Emit(kExprI32ConvertI64);
1402  }
1403  }

1407  builder_->EmitHeapType(type);

1410  bool get_local_ref(HeapType type, DataRange* data, Nullability nullable) {
1411  Var local = GetRandomLocal(data, ValueType::RefMaybeNull(type, nullable));
1412  if (local.is_valid() && (local.type.is_nullable() || locals_initialized_)) {
1413  // With a small chance don't only get the local but first "shift" local
1414  // values around. This creates more interesting patterns for the typed
1415  // optimizations.
1416  if (data->get<uint8_t>() % 8 == 1) {
1417  shift_locals_to(data, local);
1418  }
1419  builder_->EmitWithU32V(kExprLocalGet, local.index);
1420  return true;
1421  }
1422 
1423  return false;
1424  }
1425 
1426  bool new_object(HeapType type, DataRange* data, Nullability nullable) {
1427  DCHECK(type.is_index());
1428 
1429  ModuleTypeIndex index = type.ref_index();
1430  bool new_default = data->get<bool>();
1431 
1432  if (builder_->builder()->IsStructType(index)) {
1433  const StructType* struct_gen = builder_->builder()->GetStructType(index);
1434  int field_count = struct_gen->field_count();
1435  bool can_be_defaultable = std::all_of(
1436  struct_gen->fields().begin(), struct_gen->fields().end(),
1437  [](ValueType type) -> bool { return type.is_defaultable(); });
1438 
1439  if (new_default && can_be_defaultable) {
1440  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(kExprStructNewDefault);
1441  builder_->EmitU32V(index);
1442  } else {
1443  for (int i = 0; i < field_count; i++) {
1444  Generate(struct_gen->field(i).Unpacked(), data);
1445  }
1446  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(kExprStructNew);
1447  builder_->EmitU32V(index);
1448  }
1449  } else if (builder_->builder()->IsArrayType(index)) {
1450  ValueType element_type =
1451  builder_->builder()->GetArrayType(index)->element_type();
1452  bool can_be_defaultable = element_type.is_defaultable();
1453  WasmOpcode array_new_op[] = {
1454  kExprArrayNew, kExprArrayNewFixed,
1455  kExprArrayNewData, kExprArrayNewElem,
1456  kExprArrayNewDefault, // default op has to be at the end of the list.
1457  };
1458  size_t op_size = arraysize(array_new_op);
1459  if (!can_be_defaultable) --op_size;
1460  switch (array_new_op[data->get<uint8_t>() % op_size]) {
1461  case kExprArrayNewElem:
1462  case kExprArrayNewData: {
1463  // This is more restrictive than it has to be.
1464  // TODO(14034): Also support nonnullable and non-index reference
1465  // types.
1466  if (element_type.is_reference() && element_type.is_nullable() &&
1467  element_type.has_index()) {
1468  // Add a new element segment with the corresponding type.
1469  uint32_t element_segment = GenerateRefTypeElementSegment(
1470  data, builder_->builder(), element_type);
1471  // Generate offset, length.
1472  // TODO(14034): Change the distribution here to make it more likely
1473  // that the numbers are in range.
1474  Generate({kWasmI32, kWasmI32}, data);
1475  // Generate array.new_elem instruction.
1476  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(kExprArrayNewElem);
1477  builder_->EmitU32V(index);
1478  builder_->EmitU32V(element_segment);
1479  break;
1480  } else if (!element_type.is_reference()) {
1481  // Lazily create a data segment if the module doesn't have one yet.
1482  if (builder_->builder()->NumDataSegments() == 0) {
1483  GeneratePassiveDataSegment(data, builder_->builder());
1484  }
1485  int data_index =
1486  data->get<uint8_t>() % builder_->builder()->NumDataSegments();
1487  // Generate offset, length.
1488  Generate({kWasmI32, kWasmI32}, data);
1489  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(kExprArrayNewData);
1490  builder_->EmitU32V(index);
1491  builder_->EmitU32V(data_index);
1492  break;
1493  }
1494  [[fallthrough]]; // To array.new.
1495  }
1496  case kExprArrayNew:
1497  Generate(element_type.Unpacked(), data);
1498  Generate(kWasmI32, data);
1499  builder_->EmitI32Const(kMaxArraySize);
1500  builder_->Emit(kExprI32RemS);
1501  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(kExprArrayNew);
1502  builder_->EmitU32V(index);
1503  break;
1504  case kExprArrayNewFixed: {
1505  size_t element_count =
1506  std::min(static_cast<size_t>(data->get<uint8_t>()), data->size());
1507  for (size_t i = 0; i < element_count; ++i) {
1508  Generate(element_type.Unpacked(), data);
1509  }
1510  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(kExprArrayNewFixed);
1511  builder_->EmitU32V(index);
1512  builder_->EmitU32V(static_cast<uint32_t>(element_count));
1513  break;
1514  }
1515  case kExprArrayNewDefault:
1516  Generate(kWasmI32, data);
1517  builder_->EmitI32Const(kMaxArraySize);
1518  builder_->Emit(kExprI32RemS);
1519  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(kExprArrayNewDefault);
1520  builder_->EmitU32V(index);
1521  break;
1522  default:
1523  FATAL("Unimplemented opcode");
1524  }
1525  } else {
1526  CHECK(builder_->builder()->IsSignature(index));
1527  // Map the type index to a function index.
1528  // TODO(11954. 7748): Once we have type canonicalization, choose a random
1529  // function from among those matching the signature (consider function
1530  // subtyping?).
1531  uint32_t declared_func_index =
1532  index.index - static_cast<uint32_t>(arrays_.size() + structs_.size());
1533  size_t num_functions = builder_->builder()->NumDeclaredFunctions();
1534  const FunctionSig* sig = builder_->builder()->GetSignature(index);
1535  for (size_t i = 0; i < num_functions; ++i) {
1536  if (sig == builder_->builder()
1537  ->GetFunction(declared_func_index)
1538  ->signature()) {
1539  uint32_t absolute_func_index =
1540  NumImportedFunctions() + declared_func_index;
1541  builder_->EmitWithU32V(kExprRefFunc, absolute_func_index);
1542  return true;
1543  }
1544  declared_func_index = (declared_func_index + 1) % num_functions;
1545  }
1546  // We did not find a function matching the requested signature.
1547  builder_->EmitWithI32V(kExprRefNull, index.index);
1548  if (!nullable) {
1549  builder_->Emit(kExprRefAsNonNull);
1550  }
1551  }
1552 
1553  return true;
1554  }
1555 
1556  void table_op(uint32_t index, std::vector<ValueType> types, DataRange* data,
1557  WasmOpcode opcode) {
1558  DCHECK(opcode == kExprTableSet || opcode == kExprTableSize ||
1559  opcode == kExprTableGrow || opcode == kExprTableFill);
1560  for (size_t i = 0; i < types.size(); i++) {
1561  // When passing the reftype by default kWasmFuncRef is used.
1562  // Then the type is changed according to its table type.
1563  if (types[i] == kWasmFuncRef) {
1564  types[i] = builder_->builder()->GetTableType(index);
1565  }
1566  }
1567  Generate(base::VectorOf(types), data);
1568  if (opcode == kExprTableSet) {
1569  builder_->Emit(opcode);
1570  } else {
1571  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(opcode);
1572  }
1573  builder_->EmitU32V(index);
1574 
1575  // The `table_size` and `table_grow` should return an I32. However, the Wasm
1576  // instruction for table64 returns an I64, so it should be converted.
1577  if ((opcode == kExprTableSize || opcode == kExprTableGrow) &&
1578  builder_->builder()->IsTable64(index)) {
1579  builder_->Emit(kExprI32ConvertI64);
1580  }
1581  }
1582 
1583  ValueType table_address_type(int table_index) {
1584  return builder_->builder()->IsTable64(table_index) ? kWasmI64 : kWasmI32;
1585  }
1586 
1587  std::pair<int, ValueType> select_random_table(DataRange* data) {
1588  int num_tables = builder_->builder()->NumTables();
1589  DCHECK_GT(num_tables, 0);
1590  int index = data->get<uint8_t>() % num_tables;
1591  ValueType address_type = table_address_type(index);
1592 
1593  return {index, address_type};
1594  }
1595 
1596  bool table_get(HeapType type, DataRange* data, Nullability nullable) {
1597  ValueType needed_type = ValueType::RefMaybeNull(type, nullable);
1598  int table_count = builder_->builder()->NumTables();
1599  DCHECK_GT(table_count, 0);
1600  ZoneVector<uint32_t> table(builder_->builder()->zone());
1601  for (int i = 0; i < table_count; i++) {
1602  if (builder_->builder()->GetTableType(i) == needed_type) {
1603  table.push_back(i);
1604  }
1605  }
1606  if (table.empty()) {
1607  return false;
1608  }
1609  int table_index =
1610  table[data->get<uint8_t>() % static_cast<int>(table.size())];
1611  ValueType address_type = table_address_type(table_index);
1612  Generate(address_type, data);
1613  builder_->Emit(kExprTableGet);
1614  builder_->EmitU32V(table_index);
1615  return true;
1616  }
1617

1619  auto [table_index, address_type] = select_random_table(data);
1620  table_op(table_index, {address_type, kWasmFuncRef}, data, kExprTableSet);
1621  }

1623  void table_size(DataRange* data) {
1624  auto [table_index, _] = select_random_table(data);
1625  table_op(table_index, {}, data, kExprTableSize);
1626  }

1628  void table_grow(DataRange* data) {
1629  auto [table_index, address_type] = select_random_table(data);
1630  table_op(table_index, {kWasmFuncRef, address_type}, data, kExprTableGrow);
1631  }

1633  void table_fill(DataRange* data) {
1634  auto [table_index, address_type] = select_random_table(data);
1635  table_op(table_index, {address_type, kWasmFuncRef, address_type}, data,
1636  kExprTableFill);
1637  }

1639  void table_copy(DataRange* data) {
1640  ValueType needed_type = data->get<bool>() ? kWasmFuncRef : kWasmExternRef;
1641  int table_count = builder_->builder()->NumTables();
1642  ZoneVector<uint32_t> table(builder_->builder()->zone());
1643  for (int i = 0; i < table_count; i++) {
1644  if (builder_->builder()->GetTableType(i) == needed_type) {
1645  table.push_back(i);
1646  }
1647  }
1648  if (table.empty()) {
1649  return;
1650  }
1651  int first_index = data->get<uint8_t>() % static_cast<int>(table.size());
1652  int second_index = data->get<uint8_t>() % static_cast<int>(table.size());
1653  ValueType first_addrtype = table_address_type(table[first_index]);
1654  ValueType second_addrtype = table_address_type(table[second_index]);
1655  ValueType result_addrtype =
1656  first_addrtype == kWasmI32 ? kWasmI32 : second_addrtype;
1657  Generate(first_addrtype, data);
1658  Generate(second_addrtype, data);
1659  Generate(result_addrtype, data);
1660  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(kExprTableCopy);
1661  builder_->EmitU32V(table[first_index]);
1662  builder_->EmitU32V(table[second_index]);
1663  }
1664 
1665  bool array_get_helper(ValueType value_type, DataRange* data) {
1666  WasmModuleBuilder* builder = builder_->builder();
1667  ZoneVector<ModuleTypeIndex> array_indices(builder->zone());
1668 
1669  for (ModuleTypeIndex i : arrays_) {
1670  DCHECK(builder->IsArrayType(i));
1671  if (builder->GetArrayType(i)->element_type().Unpacked() == value_type) {
1672  array_indices.push_back(i);
1673  }
1674  }
1675 
1676  if (!array_indices.empty()) {
1677  int index = data->get<uint8_t>() % static_cast<int>(array_indices.size());
1678  GenerateRef(HeapType::Index(array_indices[index], kNotShared,
1679  RefTypeKind::kArray),
1680  data, kNullable);
1681  Generate(kWasmI32, data);
1682  if (builder->GetArrayType(array_indices[index])
1683  ->element_type()
1684  .is_packed()) {
1685  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(data->get<bool>() ? kExprArrayGetS
1686  : kExprArrayGetU);
1687 
1688  } else {
1689  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(kExprArrayGet);
1690  }
1691  builder_->EmitU32V(array_indices[index]);
1692  return true;
1693  }
1694 
1695  return false;
1696  }
1697 
1698  template <ValueKind wanted_kind>
1699  void array_get(DataRange* data) {
1700  bool got_array_value =
1701  array_get_helper(ValueType::Primitive(wanted_kind), data);
1702  if (!got_array_value) {
1703  Generate<wanted_kind>(data);
1704  }
1705  }
1706  bool array_get_ref(HeapType type, DataRange* data, Nullability nullable) {
1707  ValueType needed_type = ValueType::RefMaybeNull(type, nullable);
1708  return array_get_helper(needed_type, data);
1709  }

1711  void i31_get(DataRange* data) {
1712  GenerateRef(kWasmI31Ref, data);
1713  if (data->get<bool>()) {
1714  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(kExprI31GetS);
1715  } else {
1716  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(kExprI31GetU);
1717  }
1718  }
1719 
1720  void array_len(DataRange* data) {
1721  DCHECK_NE(0, arrays_.size()); // We always emit at least one array type.
1722  GenerateRef(kWasmArrayRef, data);
1723  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(kExprArrayLen);
1724  }
1725 
1726  void array_copy(DataRange* data) {
1727  DCHECK_NE(0, arrays_.size()); // We always emit at least one array type.
1728  // TODO(14034): The source element type only has to be a subtype of the
1729  // destination element type. Currently this only generates copy from same
1730  // typed arrays.
1731  ModuleTypeIndex array_index =
1732  arrays_[data->get<uint8_t>() % arrays_.size()];
1733  DCHECK(builder_->builder()->IsArrayType(array_index));
1734  GenerateRef(HeapType::Index(array_index, kNotShared, RefTypeKind::kArray),
1735  data); // destination
1736  Generate(kWasmI32, data); // destination index
1737  GenerateRef(HeapType::Index(array_index, kNotShared, RefTypeKind::kArray),
1738  data); // source
1739  Generate(kWasmI32, data); // source index
1740  Generate(kWasmI32, data); // length
1741  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(kExprArrayCopy);
1742  builder_->EmitU32V(array_index); // destination array type index
1743  builder_->EmitU32V(array_index); // source array type index
1744  }
1745 
1746  void array_fill(DataRange* data) {
1747  DCHECK_NE(0, arrays_.size()); // We always emit at least one array type.
1748  ModuleTypeIndex array_index =
1749  arrays_[data->get<uint8_t>() % arrays_.size()];
1750  DCHECK(builder_->builder()->IsArrayType(array_index));
1751  ValueType element_type = builder_->builder()
1752  ->GetArrayType(array_index)
1753  ->element_type()
1754  .Unpacked();
1755  GenerateRef(HeapType::Index(array_index, kNotShared, RefTypeKind::kArray),
1756  data); // array
1757  Generate(kWasmI32, data); // offset
1758  Generate(element_type, data); // value
1759  Generate(kWasmI32, data); // length
1760  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(kExprArrayFill);
1761  builder_->EmitU32V(array_index);
1762  }
1763 
1764  void array_init_data(DataRange* data) {
1765  DCHECK_NE(0, arrays_.size()); // We always emit at least one array type.
1766  ModuleTypeIndex array_index =
1767  arrays_[data->get<uint8_t>() % arrays_.size()];
1768  DCHECK(builder_->builder()->IsArrayType(array_index));
1769  const ArrayType* array_type =
1770  builder_->builder()->GetArrayType(array_index);
1771  DCHECK(array_type->mutability());
1772  ValueType element_type = array_type->element_type().Unpacked();
1773  if (element_type.is_reference()) {
1774  return;
1775  }
1776  if (builder_->builder()->NumDataSegments() == 0) {
1777  GeneratePassiveDataSegment(data, builder_->builder());
1778  }
1779 
1780  int data_index =
1781  data->get<uint8_t>() % builder_->builder()->NumDataSegments();
1782  // Generate array, index, data_offset, length.
1783  Generate({ValueType::RefNull(array_index, kNotShared, RefTypeKind::kArray),
1784  kWasmI32, kWasmI32, kWasmI32},
1785  data);
1786  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(kExprArrayInitData);
1787  builder_->EmitU32V(array_index);
1788  builder_->EmitU32V(data_index);
1789  }
1790 
1791  void array_init_elem(DataRange* data) {
1792  DCHECK_NE(0, arrays_.size()); // We always emit at least one array type.
1793  ModuleTypeIndex array_index =
1794  arrays_[data->get<uint8_t>() % arrays_.size()];
1795  DCHECK(builder_->builder()->IsArrayType(array_index));
1796  const ArrayType* array_type =
1797  builder_->builder()->GetArrayType(array_index);
1798  DCHECK(array_type->mutability());
1799  ValueType element_type = array_type->element_type().Unpacked();
1800  // This is more restrictive than it has to be.
1801  // TODO(14034): Also support nonnullable and non-index reference
1802  // types.
1803  if (!element_type.is_reference() || element_type.is_non_nullable() ||
1804  !element_type.has_index()) {
1805  return;
1806  }
1807  // Add a new element segment with the corresponding type.
1808  uint32_t element_segment =
1809  GenerateRefTypeElementSegment(data, builder_->builder(), element_type);
1810  // Generate array, index, elem_offset, length.
1811  // TODO(14034): Change the distribution here to make it more likely
1812  // that the numbers are in range.
1813  Generate({ValueType::RefNull(array_index, kNotShared, RefTypeKind::kArray),
1814  kWasmI32, kWasmI32, kWasmI32},
1815  data);
1816  // Generate array.new_elem instruction.
1817  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(kExprArrayInitElem);
1818  builder_->EmitU32V(array_index);
1819  builder_->EmitU32V(element_segment);
1820  }
1821 
1822  void array_set(DataRange* data) {
1823  WasmModuleBuilder* builder = builder_->builder();
1824  ZoneVector<ModuleTypeIndex> array_indices(builder->zone());
1825  for (ModuleTypeIndex i : arrays_) {
1826  DCHECK(builder->IsArrayType(i));
1827  if (builder->GetArrayType(i)->mutability()) {
1828  array_indices.push_back(i);
1829  }
1830  }
1831 
1832  if (array_indices.empty()) {
1833  return;
1834  }
1835 
1836  int index = data->get<uint8_t>() % static_cast<int>(array_indices.size());
1837  GenerateRef(
1838  HeapType::Index(array_indices[index], kNotShared, RefTypeKind::kArray),
1839  data);
1840  Generate(kWasmI32, data);
1841  Generate(
1842  builder->GetArrayType(array_indices[index])->element_type().Unpacked(),
1843  data);
1844  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(kExprArraySet);
1845  builder_->EmitU32V(array_indices[index]);
1846  }
1847 
1848  bool struct_get_helper(ValueType value_type, DataRange* data) {
1849  WasmModuleBuilder* builder = builder_->builder();
1850  ZoneVector<uint32_t> field_index(builder->zone());
1851  ZoneVector<ModuleTypeIndex> struct_index(builder->zone());
1852  for (ModuleTypeIndex i : structs_) {
1853  DCHECK(builder->IsStructType(i));
1854  int field_count = builder->GetStructType(i)->field_count();
1855  for (int index = 0; index < field_count; index++) {
1856  // TODO(14034): This should be a subtype check!
1857  if (builder->GetStructType(i)->field(index) == value_type) {
1858  field_index.push_back(index);
1859  struct_index.push_back(i);
1860  }
1861  }
1862  }
1863  if (!field_index.empty()) {
1864  int index = data->get<uint8_t>() % static_cast<int>(field_index.size());
1865  GenerateRef(HeapType::Index(struct_index[index], kNotShared,
1866  RefTypeKind::kStruct),
1867  data, kNullable);
1868  if (builder->GetStructType(struct_index[index])
1869  ->field(field_index[index])
1870  .is_packed()) {
1871  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(data->get<bool>() ? kExprStructGetS
1872  : kExprStructGetU);
1873  } else {
1874  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(kExprStructGet);
1875  }
1876  builder_->EmitU32V(struct_index[index]);
1877  builder_->EmitU32V(field_index[index]);
1878  return true;
1879  }
1880  return false;
1881  }
1882 
1883  template <ValueKind wanted_kind>
1884  void struct_get(DataRange* data) {
1885  bool got_struct_value =
1886  struct_get_helper(ValueType::Primitive(wanted_kind), data);
1887  if (!got_struct_value) {
1888  Generate<wanted_kind>(data);
1889  }
1890  }
1891 
1892  bool struct_get_ref(HeapType type, DataRange* data, Nullability nullable) {
1893  ValueType needed_type = ValueType::RefMaybeNull(type, nullable);
1894  return struct_get_helper(needed_type, data);
1895  }
1896 
1897  bool ref_cast(HeapType type, DataRange* data, Nullability nullable) {
1898  HeapType input_type = top_type(type);
1899  GenerateRef(input_type, data);
1900  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(nullable ? kExprRefCastNull : kExprRefCast);
1901  builder_->EmitHeapType(type);
1902  return true; // It always produces the desired result type.
1903  }
1904 
1905  HeapType top_type(HeapType type) {
1906  switch (type.representation()) {
1907  case HeapType::kAny:
1908  case HeapType::kEq:
1909  case HeapType::kArray:
1910  case HeapType::kStruct:
1911  case HeapType::kI31:
1912  case HeapType::kNone:
1913  return kWasmAnyRef;
1914  case HeapType::kExtern:
1915  case HeapType::kNoExtern:
1916  return kWasmExternRef;
1917  case HeapType::kExn:
1918  case HeapType::kNoExn:
1919  return kWasmExnRef;
1920  case HeapType::kFunc:
1921  case HeapType::kNoFunc:
1922  return kWasmFuncRef;
1923  default:
1924  DCHECK(type.is_index());
1925  if (builder_->builder()->IsSignature(type.ref_index())) {
1926  return kWasmFuncRef;
1927  }
1928  DCHECK(builder_->builder()->IsStructType(type.ref_index()) ||
1929  builder_->builder()->IsArrayType(type.ref_index()));
1930  return kWasmAnyRef;
1931  }
1932  }
1933 
1934  HeapType choose_sub_type(HeapType type, DataRange* data) {
1935  switch (type.representation()) {
1936  case HeapType::kAny: {
1937  constexpr GenericKind generic_types[] = {
1938  GenericKind::kAny, GenericKind::kEq, GenericKind::kArray,
1939  GenericKind::kStruct, GenericKind::kI31, GenericKind::kNone,
1940  };
1941  size_t choice =
1942  data->get<uint8_t>() %
1943  (arrays_.size() + structs_.size() + arraysize(generic_types));
1944 
1945  if (choice < arrays_.size()) {
1946  return HeapType::Index(arrays_[choice], kNotShared,
1947  RefTypeKind::kArray);
1948  }
1949  choice -= arrays_.size();
1950  if (choice < structs_.size()) {
1951  return HeapType::Index(structs_[choice], kNotShared,
1952  RefTypeKind::kStruct);
1953  }
1954  choice -= structs_.size();
1955  return HeapType::Generic(generic_types[choice], kNotShared);
1956  }
1957  case HeapType::kEq: {
1958  constexpr GenericKind generic_types[] = {
1959  GenericKind::kEq, GenericKind::kArray, GenericKind::kStruct,
1960  GenericKind::kI31, GenericKind::kNone,
1961  };
1962  size_t choice =
1963  data->get<uint8_t>() %
1964  (arrays_.size() + structs_.size() + arraysize(generic_types));
1965 
1966  if (choice < arrays_.size()) {
1967  return HeapType::Index(arrays_[choice], kNotShared,
1968  RefTypeKind::kArray);
1969  }
1970  choice -= arrays_.size();
1971  if (choice < structs_.size()) {
1972  return HeapType::Index(structs_[choice], kNotShared,
1973  RefTypeKind::kStruct);
1974  }
1975  choice -= structs_.size();
1976  return HeapType::Generic(generic_types[choice], kNotShared);
1977  }
1978  case HeapType::kStruct: {
1979  constexpr GenericKind generic_types[] = {
1980  GenericKind::kStruct,
1981  GenericKind::kNone,
1982  };
1983  const size_t type_count = structs_.size();
1984  const size_t choice =
1985  data->get<uint8_t>() % (type_count + arraysize(generic_types));
1986  return choice >= type_count
1987  ? HeapType::Generic(generic_types[choice - type_count],
1988  kNotShared)
1989  : HeapType::Index(structs_[choice], kNotShared,
1990  RefTypeKind::kStruct);
1991  }
1992  case HeapType::kArray: {
1993  constexpr GenericKind generic_types[] = {
1994  GenericKind::kArray,
1995  GenericKind::kNone,
1996  };
1997  const size_t type_count = arrays_.size();
1998  const size_t choice =
1999  data->get<uint8_t>() % (type_count + arraysize(generic_types));
2000  return choice >= type_count
2001  ? HeapType::Generic(generic_types[choice - type_count],
2002  kNotShared)
2003  : HeapType::Index(arrays_[choice], kNotShared,
2004  RefTypeKind::kArray);
2005  }
2006  case HeapType::kFunc: {
2007  constexpr GenericKind generic_types[] = {GenericKind::kFunc,
2008  GenericKind::kNoFunc};
2009  const size_t type_count = functions_.size();
2010  const size_t choice =
2011  data->get<uint8_t>() % (type_count + arraysize(generic_types));
2012  return choice >= type_count
2013  ? HeapType::Generic(generic_types[choice - type_count],
2014  kNotShared)
2015  : HeapType::Index(functions_[choice], kNotShared,
2016  RefTypeKind::kFunction);
2017  }
2018  case HeapType::kExtern:
2019  // About 10% of chosen subtypes will be kNoExtern.
2020  return HeapType::Generic(data->get<uint8_t>() > 25
2021  ? GenericKind::kExtern
2022  : GenericKind::kNoExtern,
2023  kNotShared);
2024  default:
2025  if (!type.is_index()) {
2026  // No logic implemented to find a sub-type.
2027  return type;
2028  }
2029  // Collect all (direct) sub types.
2030  // TODO(14034): Also collect indirect sub types.
2031  std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex> subtypes;
2032  uint32_t type_count = builder_->builder()->NumTypes();
2033  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < type_count; ++i) {
2034  if (builder_->builder()->GetSuperType(i) == type.ref_index()) {
2035  subtypes.push_back(ModuleTypeIndex{i});
2036  }
2037  }
2038  if (subtypes.empty()) return type; // No downcast possible.
2039  return HeapType::Index(subtypes[data->get<uint8_t>() % subtypes.size()],
2040  kNotShared, type.ref_type_kind());
2041  }
2042  }
2043 
2044  bool br_on_cast(HeapType type, DataRange* data, Nullability nullable) {
2045  DCHECK(!blocks_.empty());
2046  const uint32_t target_block = data->get<uint8_t>() % blocks_.size();
2047  const uint32_t block_index =
2048  static_cast<uint32_t>(blocks_.size()) - 1 - target_block;
2049  const auto break_types = base::VectorOf(blocks_[target_block]);
2050  if (break_types.empty()) {
2051  return false;
2052  }
2053  ValueType break_type = break_types.last();
2054  if (!break_type.is_reference()) {
2055  return false;
2056  }
2057 
2058  Generate(break_types.SubVector(0, break_types.size() - 1), data);
2059  if (data->get<bool>()) {
2060  // br_on_cast
2061  HeapType source_type = top_type(break_type.heap_type());
2062  const bool source_is_nullable = data->get<bool>();
2063  GenerateRef(source_type, data,
2064  source_is_nullable ? kNullable : kNonNullable);
2065  const bool target_is_nullable =
2066  source_is_nullable && break_type.is_nullable() && data->get<bool>();
2067  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(kExprBrOnCast);
2068  builder_->EmitU32V(source_is_nullable + (target_is_nullable << 1));
2069  builder_->EmitU32V(block_index);
2070  builder_->EmitHeapType(source_type); // source type
2071  builder_->EmitHeapType(break_type.heap_type()); // target type
2072  // Fallthrough: The type has been up-cast to the source type of the
2073  // br_on_cast instruction! (If the type on the stack was more specific,
2074  // this loses type information.)
2075  base::SmallVector<ValueType, 32> fallthrough_types(break_types);
2076  fallthrough_types.back() = ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
2077  source_type, source_is_nullable ? kNullable : kNonNullable);
2078  ConsumeAndGenerate(base::VectorOf(fallthrough_types), {}, data);
2079  // Generate the actually desired ref type.
2080  GenerateRef(type, data, nullable);
2081  } else {
2082  // br_on_cast_fail
2083  HeapType source_type = break_type.heap_type();
2084  const bool source_is_nullable = data->get<bool>();
2085  GenerateRef(source_type, data,
2086  source_is_nullable ? kNullable : kNonNullable);
2087  const bool target_is_nullable =
2088  source_is_nullable &&
2089  (!break_type.is_nullable() || data->get<bool>());
2090  HeapType target_type = choose_sub_type(source_type, data);
2091 
2092  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(kExprBrOnCastFail);
2093  builder_->EmitU32V(source_is_nullable + (target_is_nullable << 1));
2094  builder_->EmitU32V(block_index);
2095  builder_->EmitHeapType(source_type);
2096  builder_->EmitHeapType(target_type);
2097  // Fallthrough: The type has been cast to the target type.
2098  base::SmallVector<ValueType, 32> fallthrough_types(break_types);
2099  fallthrough_types.back() = ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
2100  target_type, target_is_nullable ? kNullable : kNonNullable);
2101  ConsumeAndGenerate(base::VectorOf(fallthrough_types), {}, data);
2102  // Generate the actually desired ref type.
2103  GenerateRef(type, data, nullable);
2104  }
2105  return true;
2106  }
2107 
2108  bool any_convert_extern(HeapType type, DataRange* data,
2109  Nullability nullable) {
2110  if (type.representation() != HeapType::kAny) {
2111  return false;
2112  }
2113  GenerateRef(kWasmExternRef, data);
2114  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(kExprAnyConvertExtern);
2115  if (nullable == kNonNullable) {
2116  builder_->Emit(kExprRefAsNonNull);
2117  }
2118  return true;
2119  }

2121  bool ref_as_non_null(HeapType type, DataRange* data, Nullability nullable) {
2122  GenerateRef(type, data, kNullable);

2124  return true;
2125  }

2127  void struct_set(DataRange* data) {
2128  WasmModuleBuilder* builder = builder_->builder();
2129  DCHECK_NE(0, structs_.size()); // We always emit at least one struct type.
2130  ModuleTypeIndex struct_index =
2131  structs_[data->get<uint8_t>() % structs_.size()];
2132  DCHECK(builder->IsStructType(struct_index));
2133  const StructType* struct_type = builder->GetStructType(struct_index);
2134  ZoneVector<uint32_t> field_indices(builder->zone());
2135  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < struct_type->field_count(); i++) {
2136  if (struct_type->mutability(i)) {
2137  field_indices.push_back(i);
2138  }
2139  }
2140  if (field_indices.empty()) {
2141  return;
2142  }
2143  int field_index =
2144  field_indices[data->get<uint8_t>() % field_indices.size()];
2145  GenerateRef(HeapType::Index(struct_index, kNotShared, RefTypeKind::kStruct),
2146  data);
2147  Generate(struct_type->field(field_index).Unpacked(), data);
2148  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(kExprStructSet);
2149  builder_->EmitU32V(struct_index);
2150  builder_->EmitU32V(field_index);
2151  }

2158  template <WasmOpcode opcode>
2159  void ref_test(DataRange* data) {
2160  GenerateRef(kWasmAnyRef, data);
2161  constexpr int generic_types[] = {kAnyRefCode, kEqRefCode, kArrayRefCode,
2162  kStructRefCode, kNoneCode, kI31RefCode};
2163  size_t num_types = structs_.size() + arrays_.size();
2164  size_t num_all_types = num_types + arraysize(generic_types);
2165  size_t type_choice = data->get<uint8_t>() % num_all_types;
2166  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(opcode);
2167  if (type_choice < structs_.size()) {
2168  builder_->EmitU32V(structs_[type_choice]);
2169  return;
2170  }
2171  type_choice -= structs_.size();
2172  if (type_choice < arrays_.size()) {
2173  builder_->EmitU32V(arrays_[type_choice]);
2174  return;
2175  }
2176  type_choice -= arrays_.size();
2177  builder_->EmitU32V(generic_types[type_choice]);
2178  }
