2284  void string_toutf8array(DataRange* data) {
2285  GenerateRef(kWasmExternRef, data);
2286  call_string_import(string_imports_.encodeStringToUTF8Array);
2287  }
2288 
2289  void string_fromutf8array(DataRange* data) {
2290  GenerateRef(HeapType::Index(string_imports_.array_i8, kNotShared,
2291  RefTypeKind::kArray),
2292  data);
2293  Generate(kWasmI32, data);
2294  Generate(kWasmI32, data);
2295  call_string_import(string_imports_.decodeStringFromUTF8Array);
2296  }
2297 
2298  template <typename Arr>
2299  requires requires(const Arr& arr) {
2300  { arr.size() } -> std::convertible_to<std::size_t>;
2301  { arr.data()[0] } -> std::convertible_to<GenerateFn>;
2302  }
2303  void GenerateOneOf(const Arr& alternatives, DataRange* data) {
2304  DCHECK_LT(alternatives.size(), std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max());
2305  const auto which = data->get<uint8_t>();
2306 
2307  GenerateFn alternate = alternatives[which % alternatives.size()];
2308  (this->*alternate)(data);
2309  }
2310 
2311  template <size_t... kAlternativesSizes>
2312  void GenerateOneOf(const GeneratorAlternativesPerOption<
2313  kAlternativesSizes...>& alternatives_per_option,
2314  DataRange* data) {
2315  return GenerateOneOf(alternatives_per_option.GetAlternatives(options_),
2316  data);
2317  }
2318 
2319  // Returns true if it had successfully generated a randomly chosen expression
2320  // from the `alternatives`.
2321  template <typename Arr>
2322  requires requires(const Arr& arr) {
2323  { arr.size() } -> std::convertible_to<std::size_t>;
2324  { arr.data()[0] } -> std::convertible_to<GenerateFnWithHeap>;
2325  }
2326  bool GenerateOneOf(const Arr& alternatives, HeapType type, DataRange* data,
2327  Nullability nullability) {
2328  DCHECK_LT(alternatives.size(), std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max());
2329 
2330  size_t index = data->get<uint8_t>() % (alternatives.size() + 1);
2331 
2332  if (nullability && index == alternatives.size()) {
2333  ref_null(type, data);
2334  return true;
2335  }
2336 
2337  for (size_t i = index; i < alternatives.size(); i++) {
2338  if ((this->*alternatives[i])(type, data, nullability)) {
2339  return true;
2340  }
2341  }
2342 
2343  for (size_t i = 0; i < index; i++) {
2344  if ((this->*alternatives[i])(type, data, nullability)) {
2345  return true;
2346  }
2347  }
2348 
2349  if (nullability == kNullable) {
2350  ref_null(type, data);
2351  return true;
2352  }
2353 
2354  return false;
2355  }
2356 
2357  struct GeneratorRecursionScope {
2358  explicit GeneratorRecursionScope(BodyGen* gen) : gen(gen) {
2359  ++gen->recursion_depth;
2360  DCHECK_LE(gen->recursion_depth, kMaxRecursionDepth);
2361  }
2362  ~GeneratorRecursionScope() {
2363  DCHECK_GT(gen->recursion_depth, 0);
2364  --gen->recursion_depth;
2365  }
2366  BodyGen* gen;
2367  };
2368 
2369  public:
2370  BodyGen(WasmModuleGenerationOptions options, WasmFunctionBuilder* fn,
2371  const std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex>& functions,
2372  const std::vector<ValueType>& globals,
2373  const std::vector<uint8_t>& mutable_globals,
2374  const std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex>& structs,
2375  const std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex>& arrays,
2376  const StringImports& strings, DataRange* data)
2377  : options_(options),
2378  builder_(fn),
2379  functions_(functions),
2380  globals_(globals),
2381  mutable_globals_(mutable_globals),
2382  structs_(structs),
2383  arrays_(arrays),
2384  string_imports_(strings) {
2385  const FunctionSig* sig = fn->signature();
2386  blocks_.emplace_back();
2387  for (size_t i = 0; i < sig->return_count(); ++i) {
2388  blocks_.back().push_back(sig->GetReturn(i));
2389  }
2390  locals_.resize(data->get<uint8_t>() % kMaxLocals);
2391  uint32_t num_types = static_cast<uint32_t>(
2392  functions_.size() + structs_.size() + arrays_.size());
2393  for (ValueType& local : locals_) {
2394  local = GetValueType(options, data, num_types);
2395  fn->AddLocal(local);
2396  }
2397  }
2398 
2399  int NumImportedFunctions() {
2400  return builder_->builder()->NumImportedFunctions();
2401  }
2402 
2403  // Returns the number of locals including parameters.
2404  size_t all_locals_count() const {
2405  return builder_->signature()->parameter_count() + locals_.size();
2406  }
2407 
2408  // Returns the type of the local with the given index.
2409  ValueType local_type(uint32_t index) const {
2410  size_t num_params = builder_->signature()->parameter_count();
2411  return index < num_params ? builder_->signature()->GetParam(index)
2412  : locals_[index - num_params];
2413  }
2414 
2415  // Generator functions.
2416  // Implementation detail: We define non-template Generate*TYPE*() functions
2417  // instead of templatized Generate<TYPE>(). This is because we cannot define
2418  // the templatized Generate<TYPE>() functions:
2419  // - outside of the class body without specializing the template of the
2420  // `BodyGen` (results in partial template specialization error);
2421  // - inside of the class body (gcc complains about explicit specialization in
2422  // non-namespace scope).

2500 
2501  void GenerateI32(DataRange* data) {
2502  GeneratorRecursionScope rec_scope(this);
2503  if (recursion_limit_reached() || data->size() <= 1) {
2504  // Rather than evenly distributing values across the full 32-bit range,
2505  // distribute them evenly over the possible bit lengths. In particular,
2506  // for values used as indices into something else, smaller values are
2507  // more likely to be useful.
2508  uint8_t size = 1 + (data->getPseudoRandom<uint8_t>() & 31);
2509  uint32_t mask = kMaxUInt32 >> (32 - size);
2510  builder_->EmitI32Const(data->getPseudoRandom<uint32_t>() & mask);
2511  return;
2512  }

2951  // TODO(v8:8460): v128.const is not implemented yet, and we need a way to
2952  // "bottom-out", so use a splat to generate this.

3215 
3216  void Generate(ValueType type, DataRange* data) {
3217  switch (type.kind()) {
3218  case kVoid:
3219  return GenerateVoid(data);
3220  case kI32:
3221  return GenerateI32(data);
3222  case kI64:
3223  return GenerateI64(data);
3224  case kF32:
3225  return GenerateF32(data);
3226  case kF64:
3227  return GenerateF64(data);
3228  case kS128:
3229  return GenerateS128(data);
3230  case kRefNull:
3231  return GenerateRef(type.heap_type(), data, kNullable);
3232  case kRef:
3233  return GenerateRef(type.heap_type(), data, kNonNullable);
3234  default:
3235  UNREACHABLE();
3236  }
3237  }
3238 
3239  template <ValueKind kind>
3240  constexpr void Generate(DataRange* data) {
3241  switch (kind) {
3242  case kVoid:
3243  return GenerateVoid(data);
3244  case kI32:
3245  return GenerateI32(data);
3246  case kI64:
3247  return GenerateI64(data);
3248  case kF32:
3249  return GenerateF32(data);
3250  case kF64:
3251  return GenerateF64(data);
3252  case kS128:
3253  return GenerateS128(data);
3254  default:
3255  // For kRefNull and kRef we need the HeapType which we can get from the
3256  // ValueType.
3257  UNREACHABLE();
3258  }
3259  }
3260 
3261  template <ValueKind T1, ValueKind T2, ValueKind... Ts>
3262  void Generate(DataRange* data) {
3263  // TODO(clemensb): Implement a more even split.
3264  auto first_data = data->split();
3265  Generate<T1>(&first_data);
3266  Generate<T2, Ts...>(data);
3267  }
3268 
3269  void GenerateRef(HeapType type, DataRange* data,
3270  Nullability nullability = kNullable) {
3271  std::optional<GeneratorRecursionScope> rec_scope;
3272  if (nullability) {
3273  rec_scope.emplace(this);
3274  }
3275 
3276  if (recursion_limit_reached() || data->size() == 0) {
3277  if (nullability == kNullable) {
3278  ref_null(type, data);
3279  return;
3280  }
3281  // It is ok not to return here because the non-nullable types are not
3282  // recursive by construction, so the depth is limited already.
3283  }
3284 
3285  constexpr auto alternatives_indexed_type =
3286  CreateArray(&BodyGen::new_object, //
3287  &BodyGen::get_local_ref, //
3288  &BodyGen::array_get_ref, //
3289  &BodyGen::struct_get_ref, //
3290  &BodyGen::ref_cast, //
3291  &BodyGen::ref_as_non_null, //
3292  &BodyGen::br_on_cast); //
3293 
3294  constexpr auto alternatives_func_any =
3295  CreateArray(&BodyGen::table_get, //
3296  &BodyGen::get_local_ref, //
3297  &BodyGen::array_get_ref, //
3298  &BodyGen::struct_get_ref, //
3299  &BodyGen::ref_cast, //
3300  &BodyGen::any_convert_extern, //
3301  &BodyGen::ref_as_non_null, //
3302  &BodyGen::br_on_cast); //
3303 
3304  constexpr auto alternatives_other =
3305  CreateArray(&BodyGen::array_get_ref, //
3306  &BodyGen::get_local_ref, //
3307  &BodyGen::struct_get_ref, //
3308  &BodyGen::ref_cast, //
3309  &BodyGen::ref_as_non_null, //
3310  &BodyGen::br_on_cast); //
3311 
3312  switch (type.representation()) {
3313  // For abstract types, sometimes generate one of their subtypes.
3314  case HeapType::kAny: {
3315  // Weighted according to the types in the module:
3316  // If there are D data types and F function types, the relative
3317  // frequencies for dataref is D, for funcref F, and for i31ref and
3318  // falling back to anyref 2.
3319  const uint8_t num_data_types =
3320  static_cast<uint8_t>(structs_.size() + arrays_.size());
3321  const uint8_t emit_i31ref = 2;
3322  const uint8_t fallback_to_anyref = 2;
3323  uint8_t random = data->get<uint8_t>() %
3324  (num_data_types + emit_i31ref + fallback_to_anyref);
3325  // We have to compute this first so in case GenerateOneOf fails
3326  // we will continue to fall back on an alternative that is guaranteed
3327  // to generate a value of the wanted type.
3328  // In order to know which alternative to fall back to in case
3329  // GenerateOneOf failed, the random variable is recomputed.
3330  if (random >= num_data_types + emit_i31ref) {
3331  if (GenerateOneOf(alternatives_func_any, type, data, nullability)) {
3332  return;
3333  }
3334  random = data->get<uint8_t>() % (num_data_types + emit_i31ref);
3335  }
3336  if (random < structs_.size()) {
3337  GenerateRef(kWasmStructRef, data, nullability);
3338  } else if (random < num_data_types) {
3339  GenerateRef(kWasmArrayRef, data, nullability);
3340  } else {
3341  GenerateRef(kWasmI31Ref, data, nullability);
3342  }
3343  return;
3344  }
3345  case HeapType::kArray: {
3346  constexpr uint8_t fallback_to_dataref = 1;
3347  uint8_t random =
3348  data->get<uint8_t>() % (arrays_.size() + fallback_to_dataref);
3349  // Try generating one of the alternatives and continue to the rest of
3350  // the methods in case it fails.
3351  if (random >= arrays_.size()) {
3352  if (GenerateOneOf(alternatives_other, type, data, nullability))
3353  return;
3354  random = data->get<uint8_t>() % arrays_.size();
3355  }
3356  ModuleTypeIndex index = arrays_[random];
3357  DCHECK(builder_->builder()->IsArrayType(index));
3358  GenerateRef(HeapType::Index(index, kNotShared, RefTypeKind::kArray),
3359  data, nullability);
3360  return;
3361  }
3362  case HeapType::kStruct: {
3363  constexpr uint8_t fallback_to_dataref = 2;
3364  uint8_t random =
3365  data->get<uint8_t>() % (structs_.size() + fallback_to_dataref);
3366  // Try generating one of the alternatives
3367  // and continue to the rest of the methods in case it fails.
3368  if (random >= structs_.size()) {
3369  if (GenerateOneOf(alternatives_other, type, data, nullability)) {
3370  return;
3371  }
3372  random = data->get<uint8_t>() % structs_.size();
3373  }
3374  ModuleTypeIndex index = structs_[random];
3375  DCHECK(builder_->builder()->IsStructType(index));
3376  GenerateRef(HeapType::Index(index, kNotShared, RefTypeKind::kStruct),
3377  data, nullability);
3378  return;
3379  }
3380  case HeapType::kEq: {
3381  const uint8_t num_types = arrays_.size() + structs_.size();
3382  const uint8_t emit_i31ref = 2;
3383  constexpr uint8_t fallback_to_eqref = 1;
3384  uint8_t random = data->get<uint8_t>() %
3385  (num_types + emit_i31ref + fallback_to_eqref);
3386  // Try generating one of the alternatives
3387  // and continue to the rest of the methods in case it fails.
3388  if (random >= num_types + emit_i31ref) {
3389  if (GenerateOneOf(alternatives_other, type, data, nullability)) {
3390  return;
3391  }
3392  random = data->get<uint8_t>() % (num_types + emit_i31ref);
3393  }
3394  if (random < num_types) {
3395  // Using `HeapType(random)` here relies on the assumption that struct
3396  // and array types come before signatures.
3397  RefTypeKind kind = RefTypeKind::kOther;
3398  if (builder_->builder()->IsArrayType(random)) {
3399  kind = RefTypeKind::kArray;
3400  } else if (builder_->builder()->IsStructType(random)) {
3401  kind = RefTypeKind::kStruct;
3402  } else {
3403  UNREACHABLE();
3404  }
3405  GenerateRef(
3406  HeapType::Index(ModuleTypeIndex{random}, kNotShared, kind), data,
3407  nullability);
3408  } else {
3409  GenerateRef(kWasmI31Ref, data, nullability);
3410  }
3411  return;
3412  }
3413  case HeapType::kFunc: {
3414  uint32_t random = data->get<uint8_t>() % (functions_.size() + 1);
3415  /// Try generating one of the alternatives
3416  // and continue to the rest of the methods in case it fails.
3417  if (random >= functions_.size()) {
3418  if (GenerateOneOf(alternatives_func_any, type, data, nullability)) {
3419  return;
3420  }
3421  random = data->get<uint8_t>() % functions_.size();
3422  }
3423  ModuleTypeIndex signature_index = functions_[random];
3424  DCHECK(builder_->builder()->IsSignature(signature_index));
3425  GenerateRef(HeapType::Index(signature_index, kNotShared,
3426  RefTypeKind::kFunction),
3427  data, nullability);
3428  return;
3429  }
3430  case HeapType::kI31: {
3431  // Try generating one of the alternatives
3432  // and continue to the rest of the methods in case it fails.
3433  if (data->get<bool>() &&
3434  GenerateOneOf(alternatives_other, type, data, nullability)) {
3435  return;
3436  }
3437  Generate(kWasmI32, data);
3438  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(kExprRefI31);
3439  return;
3440  }
3441  case HeapType::kExn: {
3442  // TODO(manoskouk): Can we somehow come up with a nontrivial exnref?
3443  ref_null(type, data);
3444  if (nullability == kNonNullable) {
3445  builder_->Emit(kExprRefAsNonNull);
3446  }
3447  return;
3448  }
3449  case HeapType::kExtern: {
3450  uint8_t choice = data->get<uint8_t>();
3451  if (choice < 25) {
3452  // ~10% chance of extern.convert_any.
3453  GenerateRef(kWasmAnyRef, data);
3454  builder_->EmitWithPrefix(kExprExternConvertAny);
3455  if (nullability == kNonNullable) {
3456  builder_->Emit(kExprRefAsNonNull);
3457  }
3458  return;
3459  }
3460  // ~80% chance of string.
3461  if (choice < 230 && options_.generate_wasm_gc()) {
3462  uint8_t subchoice = choice % 7;
3463  switch (subchoice) {
3464  case 0:
3465  return string_cast(data);
3466  case 1:
3467  return string_fromcharcode(data);
3468  case 2:
3469  return string_fromcodepoint(data);
3470  case 3:
3471  return string_concat(data);
3472  case 4:
3473  return string_substring(data);
3474  case 5:
3475  return string_fromcharcodearray(data);
3476  case 6:
3477  return string_fromutf8array(data);
3478  }
3479  }
3480  // ~10% chance of fallthrough.
3481  [[fallthrough]];
3482  }
3483  case HeapType::kNoExtern:
3484  case HeapType::kNoFunc:
3485  case HeapType::kNone:
3486  case HeapType::kNoExn:
3487  ref_null(type, data);
3488  if (nullability == kNonNullable) {
3489  builder_->Emit(kExprRefAsNonNull);
3490  }
3491  return;
3492  default:
3493  // Indexed type (i.e. user-defined type).
3494  DCHECK(type.is_index());
3495  if (options_.generate_wasm_gc() &&
3496  type.ref_index() == string_imports_.array_i8 &&
3497  data->get<uint8_t>() < 32) {
3498  // 1/8th chance, fits the number of remaining alternatives (7) well.
3499  return string_toutf8array(data);
3500  }
3501  GenerateOneOf(alternatives_indexed_type, type, data, nullability);
3502  return;
3503  }
3504  UNREACHABLE();
3505  }
3506 
3507  void GenerateRef(DataRange* data) {
3508  constexpr HeapType top_types[] = {
3509  kWasmAnyRef,
3510  kWasmFuncRef,
3511  kWasmExternRef,
3512  };
3513  HeapType type = top_types[data->get<uint8_t>() % arraysize(top_types)];
3514  GenerateRef(type, data);
3515  }
3516 
3517  std::vector<ValueType> GenerateTypes(DataRange* data) {
3518  return fuzzing::GenerateTypes(
3519  options_, data,
3520  static_cast<uint32_t>(functions_.size() + structs_.size() +
3521  arrays_.size()));
3522  }
3523 
3524  void Generate(base::Vector<const ValueType> types, DataRange* data) {
3525  // Maybe emit a multi-value block with the expected return type. Use a
3526  // non-default value to indicate block generation to avoid recursion when we
3527  // reach the end of the data.
3528  bool generate_block = data->get<uint8_t>() % 32 == 1;
3529  if (generate_block) {
3530  GeneratorRecursionScope rec_scope(this);
3531  if (!recursion_limit_reached()) {
3532  const auto param_types = GenerateTypes(data);
3533  Generate(base::VectorOf(param_types), data);
3534  any_block(base::VectorOf(param_types), types, data);
3535  return;
3536  }
3537  }
3538 
3539  if (types.size() == 0) {
3540  Generate(kWasmVoid, data);
3541  return;
3542  }
3543  if (types.size() == 1) {
3544  Generate(types[0], data);
3545  return;
3546  }
3547 
3548  // Split the types in two halves and recursively generate each half.
3549  // Each half is non empty to ensure termination.
3550  size_t split_index = data->get<uint8_t>() % (types.size() - 1) + 1;
3551  base::Vector<const ValueType> lower_half = types.SubVector(0, split_index);
3552  base::Vector<const ValueType> upper_half =
3553  types.SubVector(split_index, types.size());
3554  DataRange first_range = data->split();
3555  Generate(lower_half, &first_range);
3556  Generate(upper_half, data);
3557  }
3558  void Generate(std::initializer_list<ValueTypeBase> types, DataRange* data) {
3559  base::Vector<const ValueType> cast_types = base::VectorOf<const ValueType>(
3560  static_cast<const ValueType*>(types.begin()), types.size());
3561  return Generate(cast_types, data);
3562  }
3563 
3564  void Consume(ValueType type) {
3565  // Try to store the value in a local if there is a local with the same
3566  // type. TODO(14034): For reference types a local with a super type
3567  // would also be fine.
3568  size_t num_params = builder_->signature()->parameter_count();
3569  for (uint32_t local_offset = 0; local_offset < locals_.size();
3570  ++local_offset) {
3571  if (locals_[local_offset] == type) {
3572  uint32_t local_index = static_cast<uint32_t>(local_offset + num_params);
3573  builder_->EmitWithU32V(kExprLocalSet, local_index);
3574  return;
3575  }
3576  }
3577  for (uint32_t param_index = 0; param_index < num_params; ++param_index) {
3578  if (builder_->signature()->GetParam(param_index) == type) {
3579  builder_->EmitWithU32V(kExprLocalSet, param_index);
3580  return;
3581  }
3582  }
3583  // No opportunity found to use the value, so just drop it.
3584  builder_->Emit(kExprDrop);
3585  }
3586 
3587  // Emit code to match an arbitrary signature.
3588  // TODO(11954): Add the missing reference type conversion/upcasting.
3589  void ConsumeAndGenerate(base::Vector<const ValueType> param_types,
3590  base::Vector<const ValueType> return_types,
3591  DataRange* data) {
3592  // This numeric conversion logic consists of picking exactly one
3593  // index in the return values and dropping all the values that come
3594  // before that index. Then we convert the value from that index to the
3595  // wanted type. If we don't find any value we generate it.
3596  auto primitive = [](ValueType t) -> bool {
3597  switch (t.kind()) {
3598  case kI32:
3599  case kI64:
3600  case kF32:
3601  case kF64:
3602  return true;
3603  default:
3604  return false;
3605  }
3606  };
3607 
3608  if (return_types.size() == 0 || param_types.size() == 0 ||
3609  !primitive(return_types[0])) {
3610  for (auto iter = param_types.rbegin(); iter != param_types.rend();
3611  ++iter) {
3612  Consume(*iter);
3613  }
3614  Generate(return_types, data);
3615  return;
3616  }
3617 
3618  int bottom_primitives = 0;
3619 
3620  while (static_cast<int>(param_types.size()) > bottom_primitives &&
3621  primitive(param_types[bottom_primitives])) {
3622  bottom_primitives++;
3623  }
3624  int return_index =
3625  bottom_primitives > 0 ? (data->get<uint8_t>() % bottom_primitives) : -1;
3626  for (int i = static_cast<int>(param_types.size() - 1); i > return_index;
3627  --i) {
3628  Consume(param_types[i]);
3629  }
3630  for (int i = return_index; i > 0; --i) {
3631  Convert(param_types[i], param_types[i - 1]);
3632  builder_->EmitI32Const(0);
3633  builder_->Emit(kExprSelect);
3634  }
3635  DCHECK(!return_types.empty());
3636  if (return_index >= 0) {
3637  Convert(param_types[0], return_types[0]);
3638  Generate(return_types + 1, data);
3639  } else {
3640  Generate(return_types, data);
3641  }
3642  }
3643 
3644  void InitializeNonDefaultableLocals(DataRange* data) {
3645  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < locals_.size(); i++) {
3646  if (!locals_[i].is_defaultable()) {
3647  GenerateRef(locals_[i].heap_type(), data, kNonNullable);
3648  builder_->EmitWithU32V(
3649  kExprLocalSet, i + static_cast<uint32_t>(
3650  builder_->signature()->parameter_count()));
3651  }
3652  }
3653  locals_initialized_ = true;
3654  }
3655 
3656  private:
3657  bool recursion_limit_reached() {
3658  return recursion_depth >= kMaxRecursionDepth;
3659  }
3660 
3661  const WasmModuleGenerationOptions options_;
3662  WasmFunctionBuilder* const builder_;
3663  std::vector<std::vector<ValueType>> blocks_;
3664  const std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex>& functions_;
3665  std::vector<ValueType> locals_;
3666  std::vector<ValueType> globals_;
3667  std::vector<uint8_t> mutable_globals_; // indexes into {globals_}.
3668  uint32_t recursion_depth = 0;
3669  std::vector<int> catch_blocks_;
3670  const std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex>& structs_;
3671  const std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex>& arrays_;
3672  const StringImports& string_imports_;
3673  bool locals_initialized_ = false;
3674 };

3676 WasmInitExpr GenerateInitExpr(Zone* zone, DataRange& range,
3677  WasmModuleBuilder* builder, ValueType type,
3678  const std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex>& structs,
3679  const std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex>& arrays,
3680  uint32_t recursion_depth);

3682 class ModuleGen {
3683  public:
3684  explicit ModuleGen(Zone* zone, WasmModuleGenerationOptions options,
3685  WasmModuleBuilder* fn, DataRange* module_range,
3686  uint8_t num_functions, uint8_t num_structs,
3687  uint8_t num_arrays, uint8_t num_signatures)
3688  : zone_(zone),
3689  options_(options),
3690  builder_(fn),
3691  module_range_(module_range),
3692  num_functions_(num_functions),
3693  num_structs_(num_structs),
3694  num_arrays_(num_arrays),
3695  num_types_(num_signatures + num_structs + num_arrays) {}
3696 
3697  // Generates and adds random number of memories.
3698  void GenerateRandomMemories() {
3699  int num_memories = 1 + (module_range_->get<uint8_t>() % kMaxMemories);
3700  for (int i = 0; i < num_memories; i++) {
3701  uint8_t random_byte = module_range_->get<uint8_t>();
3702  bool mem64 = random_byte & 1;
3703  bool has_maximum = random_byte & 2;
3704  static_assert(kV8MaxWasmMemory64Pages <= kMaxUInt32);
3705  uint32_t max_supported_pages =
3706  mem64 ? max_mem64_pages() : max_mem32_pages();
3707  uint32_t min_pages =
3708  module_range_->get<uint32_t>() % (max_supported_pages + 1);
3709  if (has_maximum) {
3710  uint32_t max_pages =
3711  std::max(min_pages, module_range_->get<uint32_t>() %
3712  (max_supported_pages + 1));
3713  if (mem64) {
3714  builder_->AddMemory64(min_pages, max_pages);
3715  } else {
3716  builder_->AddMemory(min_pages, max_pages);
3717  }
3718  } else {
3719  if (mem64) {
3720  builder_->AddMemory64(min_pages);
3721  } else {
3722  builder_->AddMemory(min_pages);
3723  }
3724  }
3725  }
3726  }
3727 
3728  // Puts the types into random recursive groups.
3729  std::map<uint8_t, uint8_t> GenerateRandomRecursiveGroups(
3730  uint8_t kNumDefaultArrayTypes) {
3731  // (Type_index -> end of explicit rec group).
3732  std::map<uint8_t, uint8_t> explicit_rec_groups;
3733  uint8_t current_type_index = 0;
3734 
3735  // The default array types are each in their own recgroup.
3736  for (uint8_t i = 0; i < kNumDefaultArrayTypes; i++) {
3737  explicit_rec_groups.emplace(current_type_index, current_type_index);
3738  builder_->AddRecursiveTypeGroup(current_type_index++, 1);
3739  }
3740 
3741  while (current_type_index < num_types_) {
3742  // First, pick a random start for the next group. We allow it to be
3743  // beyond the end of types (i.e., we add no further recursive groups).
3744  uint8_t group_start = module_range_->get<uint8_t>() %
3745  (num_types_ - current_type_index + 1) +
3746  current_type_index;
3747  DCHECK_GE(group_start, current_type_index);
3748  current_type_index = group_start;
3749  if (group_start < num_types_) {
3750  // If we did not reach the end of the types, pick a random group size.
3751  uint8_t group_size =
3752  module_range_->get<uint8_t>() % (num_types_ - group_start) + 1;
3753  DCHECK_LE(group_start + group_size, num_types_);
3754  for (uint8_t i = group_start; i < group_start + group_size; i++) {
3755  explicit_rec_groups.emplace(i, group_start + group_size - 1);
3756  }
3757  builder_->AddRecursiveTypeGroup(group_start, group_size);
3758  current_type_index += group_size;
3759  }
3760  }
3761  return explicit_rec_groups;
3762  }
3763 
3764  // Generates and adds random struct types.
3765  void GenerateRandomStructs(
3766  const std::map<uint8_t, uint8_t>& explicit_rec_groups,
3767  std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex>& struct_types, uint8_t& current_type_index,
3768  uint8_t kNumDefaultArrayTypes) {
3769  uint8_t last_struct_type_index = current_type_index + num_structs_;
3770  for (; current_type_index < last_struct_type_index; current_type_index++) {
3771  auto rec_group = explicit_rec_groups.find(current_type_index);
3772  uint8_t current_rec_group_end = rec_group != explicit_rec_groups.end()
3773  ? rec_group->second
3774  : current_type_index;
3775 
3776  ModuleTypeIndex supertype = kNoSuperType;
3777  uint8_t num_fields =
3778  module_range_->get<uint8_t>() % (kMaxStructFields + 1);
3779 
3780  uint32_t existing_struct_types =
3781  current_type_index - kNumDefaultArrayTypes;
3782  if (existing_struct_types > 0 && module_range_->get<bool>()) {
3783  supertype = ModuleTypeIndex{module_range_->get<uint8_t>() %
3784  existing_struct_types +
3785  kNumDefaultArrayTypes};
3786  num_fields += builder_->GetStructType(supertype)->field_count();
3787  }
3788  // TODO(403372470): Add support for custom descriptors.
3789  // TODO(42204563): Add support for shared structs.
3790  StructType::Builder struct_builder(zone_, num_fields, false, false);
3791 
3792  // Add all fields from super type.
3793  uint32_t field_index = 0;
3794  if (supertype != kNoSuperType) {
3795  const StructType* parent = builder_->GetStructType(supertype);
3796  for (; field_index < parent->field_count(); ++field_index) {
3797  // TODO(14034): This could also be any sub type of the supertype's
3798  // element type.
3799  struct_builder.AddField(parent->field(field_index),
3800  parent->mutability(field_index));
3801  }
3802  }
3803  for (; field_index < num_fields; field_index++) {
3804  // Notes:
3805  // - We allow a type to only have non-nullable fields of types that
3806  // are defined earlier. This way we avoid infinite non-nullable
3807  // constructions. Also relevant for arrays and functions.
3808  // - On the other hand, nullable fields can be picked up to the end of
3809  // the current recursive group.
3810  // - We exclude the non-nullable generic types arrayref, anyref,
3811  // structref, eqref and externref from the fields of structs and
3812  // arrays. This is so that GenerateInitExpr has a way to break a
3813  // recursion between a struct/array field and those types
3814  // ((ref extern) gets materialized through (ref any)).
3815  ValueType type = GetValueTypeHelper(
3816  options_, module_range_, current_rec_group_end + 1,
3817  current_type_index, kIncludeNumericTypes, kIncludePackedTypes,
3818  kExcludeSomeGenerics);
3819 
3820  bool mutability = module_range_->get<bool>();
3821  struct_builder.AddField(type, mutability);
3822  }
3823  StructType* struct_fuz = struct_builder.Build();
3824  // TODO(14034): Generate some final types too.
3825  ModuleTypeIndex index =
3826  builder_->AddStructType(struct_fuz, false, supertype);
3827  struct_types.push_back(index);
3828  }
3829  }
3830 
3831  // Creates and adds random array types.
3832  void GenerateRandomArrays(
3833  const std::map<uint8_t, uint8_t>& explicit_rec_groups,
3834  std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex>& array_types, uint8_t& current_type_index) {
3835  uint32_t last_struct_type_index = current_type_index + num_structs_;
3836  for (; current_type_index < num_structs_ + num_arrays_;
3837  current_type_index++) {
3838  auto rec_group = explicit_rec_groups.find(current_type_index);
3839  uint8_t current_rec_group_end = rec_group != explicit_rec_groups.end()
3840  ? rec_group->second
3841  : current_type_index;
3842  ValueType type =
3843  GetValueTypeHelper(options_, module_range_, current_rec_group_end + 1,
3844  current_type_index, kIncludeNumericTypes,
3845  kIncludePackedTypes, kExcludeSomeGenerics);
3846  ModuleTypeIndex supertype = kNoSuperType;
3847  if (current_type_index > last_struct_type_index &&
3848  module_range_->get<bool>()) {
3849  // Do not include the default array types, because they are final.
3850  uint8_t existing_array_types =
3851  current_type_index - last_struct_type_index;
3852  supertype = ModuleTypeIndex{
3853  last_struct_type_index +
3854  (module_range_->get<uint8_t>() % existing_array_types)};
3855  // TODO(14034): This could also be any sub type of the supertype's
3856  // element type.
3857  type = builder_->GetArrayType(supertype)->element_type();
3858  }
3859  ArrayType* array_fuz = zone_->New<ArrayType>(type, true);
3860  // TODO(14034): Generate some final types too.
3861  ModuleTypeIndex index =
3862  builder_->AddArrayType(array_fuz, false, supertype);
3863  array_types.push_back(index);
3864  }
3865  }
3866 
3867  enum SigKind { kFunctionSig, kExceptionSig };
3868 
3869  FunctionSig* GenerateSig(SigKind sig_kind, int num_types) {
3870  // Generate enough parameters to spill some to the stack.
3871  int num_params = int{module_range_->get<uint8_t>()} % (kMaxParameters + 1);
3872  int num_returns =
3873  sig_kind == kFunctionSig
3874  ? int{module_range_->get<uint8_t>()} % (kMaxReturns + 1)
3875  : 0;
3876 
3877  FunctionSig::Builder builder(zone_, num_returns, num_params);
3878  for (int i = 0; i < num_returns; ++i) {
3879  builder.AddReturn(GetValueType(options_, module_range_, num_types));
3880  }
3881  for (int i = 0; i < num_params; ++i) {
3882  builder.AddParam(GetValueType(options_, module_range_, num_types));
3883  }
3884  return builder.Get();
3885  }
3886 
3887  // Creates and adds random function signatures.
3888  void GenerateRandomFunctionSigs(
3889  const std::map<uint8_t, uint8_t>& explicit_rec_groups,
3890  std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex>& function_signatures,
3891  uint8_t& current_type_index, bool kIsFinal) {
3892  // Recursive groups consist of recursive types that came with the WasmGC
3893  // proposal.
3894  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!options_.generate_wasm_gc(), explicit_rec_groups.empty());
3895 
3896  for (; current_type_index < num_types_; current_type_index++) {
3897  auto rec_group = explicit_rec_groups.find(current_type_index);
3898  uint8_t current_rec_group_end = rec_group != explicit_rec_groups.end()
3899  ? rec_group->second
3900  : current_type_index;
3901  FunctionSig* sig = GenerateSig(kFunctionSig, current_rec_group_end + 1);
3902  ModuleTypeIndex signature_index =
3903  builder_->ForceAddSignature(sig, kIsFinal);
3904  function_signatures.push_back(signature_index);
3905  }
3906  }

3908  void GenerateRandomExceptions(uint8_t num_exceptions) {

3910  FunctionSig* sig = GenerateSig(kExceptionSig, num_types_);
3911  builder_->AddTag(sig);
3912  }

3918  static constexpr ModuleTypeIndex kArrayI16{1};
3919  StringImports strings;
3920  strings.array_i8 = kArrayI8;
3921  strings.array_i16 = kArrayI16;

3923  static constexpr ValueType kExternRef = kWasmExternRef;
3924  static constexpr ValueType kI32 = kWasmI32;
3925  static constexpr ValueType kRefA8 =

3930  ValueType::RefNull(kArrayI16, kNotShared, RefTypeKind::kArray);

3933  // "e" = non-nullable "ref extern".

3936  kExternRef};

3938  kI32};

3940  static constexpr ValueType kReps_i_rr[] = {kI32, kExternRef, kExternRef};
3941  static constexpr ValueType kReps_from_a16[] = {kRefExtern, kRefNullA16,
3942  kI32, kI32};
3943  static constexpr ValueType kReps_from_a8[] = {kRefExtern, kRefNullA8, kI32,
3944  kI32};
3945  static constexpr ValueType kReps_into_a16[] = {kI32, kExternRef,
3946  kRefNullA16, kI32};
3947  static constexpr ValueType kReps_into_a8[] = {kI32, kExternRef, kRefNullA8,

3950 
3951  static constexpr FunctionSig kSig_e_i(1, 1, kReps_e_i);
3952  static constexpr FunctionSig kSig_e_r(1, 1, kReps_e_rr);
3953  static constexpr FunctionSig kSig_e_rr(1, 2, kReps_e_rr);
3954  static constexpr FunctionSig kSig_e_rii(1, 3, kReps_e_rii);
3955 
3956  static constexpr FunctionSig kSig_i_r(1, 1, kReps_i_ri);
3957  static constexpr FunctionSig kSig_i_ri(1, 2, kReps_i_ri);
3958  static constexpr FunctionSig kSig_i_rr(1, 2, kReps_i_rr);
3959  static constexpr FunctionSig kSig_from_a16(1, 3, kReps_from_a16);
3960  static constexpr FunctionSig kSig_from_a8(1, 3, kReps_from_a8);

3962  static constexpr FunctionSig kSig_into_a8(1, 3, kReps_into_a8);

3971

3975  STRINGFUNC(cast, kSig_e_r, kJsString);
