3989  STRINGFUNC(encodeStringIntoUTF8Array, kSig_into_a8, kTextEncoder);
3990  STRINGFUNC(encodeStringToUTF8Array, kSig_to_a8, kTextEncoder);
3991  STRINGFUNC(decodeStringFromUTF8Array, kSig_from_a8, kTextDecoder);
3992 
3993 #undef STRINGFUNC
3994 
3995  return strings;
3996  }
3997 
3998  // Creates and adds random tables.
3999  void GenerateRandomTables(const std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex>& array_types,
4000  const std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex>& struct_types) {
4001  int num_tables = module_range_->get<uint8_t>() % kMaxTables + 1;
4002  int are_table64 = module_range_->get<uint8_t>();
4003  static_assert(
4004  kMaxTables <= 8,
4005  "Too many tables. Use more random bits to choose their address type.");
4006  const int max_table_size = MaxTableSize();
4007  for (int i = 0; i < num_tables; i++) {
4008  uint32_t min_size = i == 0
4009  ? num_functions_
4010  : module_range_->get<uint8_t>() % max_table_size;
4011  uint32_t max_size =
4012  module_range_->get<uint8_t>() % (max_table_size - min_size) +
4013  min_size;
4014  // Table 0 is always funcref. This guarantees that
4015  // - call_indirect has at least one funcref table to work with,
4016  // - we have a place to reference all functions in the program, so they
4017  // count as "declared" for ref.func.
4018  bool force_funcref = i == 0;
4019  ValueType type =
4020  force_funcref
4021  ? kWasmFuncRef
4022  : GetValueTypeHelper(options_, module_range_, num_types_,
4023  num_types_, kExcludeNumericTypes,
4024  kExcludePackedTypes, kIncludeAllGenerics);
4025  bool use_initializer =
4026  !type.is_defaultable() || module_range_->get<bool>();
4027 
4028  bool use_table64 = are_table64 & 1;
4029  are_table64 >>= 1;
4030  AddressType address_type =
4031  use_table64 ? AddressType::kI64 : AddressType::kI32;
4032  uint32_t table_index =
4033  use_initializer
4034  ? builder_->AddTable(
4035  type, min_size, max_size,
4036  GenerateInitExpr(zone_, *module_range_, builder_, type,
4037  struct_types, array_types, 0),
4038  address_type)
4039  : builder_->AddTable(type, min_size, max_size, address_type);
4040  if (type.is_reference_to(HeapType::kFunc)) {
4041  // For function tables, initialize them with functions from the program.
4042  // Currently, the fuzzer assumes that every funcref/(ref func) table
4043  // contains the functions in the program in the order they are defined.
4044  // TODO(11954): Consider generalizing this.
4045  WasmInitExpr init_expr = builder_->IsTable64(table_index)
4046  ? WasmInitExpr(static_cast<int64_t>(0))
4047  : WasmInitExpr(static_cast<int32_t>(0));
4048  WasmModuleBuilder::WasmElemSegment segment(zone_, type, table_index,
4049  init_expr);
4050  for (int entry_index = 0; entry_index < static_cast<int>(min_size);
4051  entry_index++) {
4052  segment.entries.emplace_back(
4053  WasmModuleBuilder::WasmElemSegment::Entry::kRefFuncEntry,
4054  builder_->NumImportedFunctions() +
4055  (entry_index % num_functions_));
4056  }
4057  builder_->AddElementSegment(std::move(segment));
4058  }
4059  }
4060  }
4061 
4062  // Creates and adds random globals.
4063  std::tuple<std::vector<ValueType>, std::vector<uint8_t>>
4064  GenerateRandomGlobals(const std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex>& array_types,
4065  const std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex>& struct_types) {
4066  int num_globals = module_range_->get<uint8_t>() % (kMaxGlobals + 1);
4067  std::vector<ValueType> globals;
4068  std::vector<uint8_t> mutable_globals;
4069  globals.reserve(num_globals);
4070  mutable_globals.reserve(num_globals);
4071 
4072  for (int i = 0; i < num_globals; ++i) {
4073  ValueType type = GetValueType(options_, module_range_, num_types_);
4074  // 1/8 of globals are immutable.
4075  const bool mutability = (module_range_->get<uint8_t>() % 8) != 0;
4076  builder_->AddGlobal(type, mutability,
4077  GenerateInitExpr(zone_, *module_range_, builder_,
4078  type, struct_types, array_types, 0));
4079  globals.push_back(type);
4080  if (mutability) mutable_globals.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(i));
4081  }
4082 
4083  return {globals, mutable_globals};
4084  }
4085 
4086  private:
4087  Zone* const zone_;
4088  const WasmModuleGenerationOptions options_;
4089  WasmModuleBuilder* const builder_;
4090  DataRange* const module_range_;
4091  const uint8_t num_functions_;
4092  const uint8_t num_structs_;
4093  const uint8_t num_arrays_;
4094  const uint16_t num_types_;
4095 };
4096 
4097 WasmInitExpr GenerateStructNewInitExpr(
4098  Zone* zone, DataRange& range, WasmModuleBuilder* builder,
4099  ModuleTypeIndex index, const std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex>& structs,
4100  const std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex>& arrays, uint32_t recursion_depth) {
4101  const StructType* struct_type = builder->GetStructType(index);
4102  bool use_new_default =
4103  std::all_of(struct_type->fields().begin(), struct_type->fields().end(),
4104  [](ValueType type) { return type.is_defaultable(); }) &&
4105  range.get<bool>();
4106 
4107  if (use_new_default) {
4108  return WasmInitExpr::StructNewDefault(index);
4109  } else {
4110  ZoneVector<WasmInitExpr>* elements =
4111  zone->New<ZoneVector<WasmInitExpr>>(zone);
4112  int field_count = struct_type->field_count();
4113  for (int field_index = 0; field_index < field_count; field_index++) {
4114  elements->push_back(GenerateInitExpr(
4115  zone, range, builder, struct_type->field(field_index), structs,
4116  arrays, recursion_depth + 1));
4117  }
4118  return WasmInitExpr::StructNew(index, elements);
4119  }
4120 }
4121 
4122 WasmInitExpr GenerateArrayInitExpr(Zone* zone, DataRange& range,
4123  WasmModuleBuilder* builder,
4124  ModuleTypeIndex index,
4125  const std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex>& structs,
4126  const std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex>& arrays,
4127  uint32_t recursion_depth) {
4128  constexpr int kMaxArrayLength = 20;
4129  uint8_t choice = range.get<uint8_t>() % 3;
4130  ValueType element_type = builder->GetArrayType(index)->element_type();
4131  if (choice == 0) {
4132  size_t element_count = range.get<uint8_t>() % kMaxArrayLength;
4133  if (!element_type.is_defaultable()) {
4134  // If the element type is not defaultable, limit the size to 0 or 1
4135  // to prevent having to create too many such elements on the value
4136  // stack. (With multiple non-nullable references, this can explode
4137  // in size very quickly.)
4138  element_count %= 2;
4139  }
4140  ZoneVector<WasmInitExpr>* elements =
4141  zone->New<ZoneVector<WasmInitExpr>>(zone);
4142  for (size_t i = 0; i < element_count; i++) {
4143  elements->push_back(GenerateInitExpr(zone, range, builder, element_type,
4144  structs, arrays,
4145  recursion_depth + 1));
4146  }
4147  return WasmInitExpr::ArrayNewFixed(index, elements);
4148  } else if (choice == 1 || !element_type.is_defaultable()) {
4149  // TODO(14034): Add other int expressions to length (same below).
4150  WasmInitExpr length = WasmInitExpr(range.get<uint8_t>() % kMaxArrayLength);
4151  WasmInitExpr init = GenerateInitExpr(zone, range, builder, element_type,
4152  structs, arrays, recursion_depth + 1);
4153  return WasmInitExpr::ArrayNew(zone, index, init, length);
4154  } else {
4155  WasmInitExpr length = WasmInitExpr(range.get<uint8_t>() % kMaxArrayLength);
4156  return WasmInitExpr::ArrayNewDefault(zone, index, length);
4157  }
4158 }
4159 
4160 WasmInitExpr GenerateInitExpr(Zone* zone, DataRange& range,
4161  WasmModuleBuilder* builder, ValueType type,
4162  const std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex>& structs,
4163  const std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex>& arrays,
4164  uint32_t recursion_depth) {
4165  switch (type.kind()) {
4166  case kI8:
4167  case kI16:
4168  case kI32: {
4169  if (range.size() == 0 || recursion_depth >= kMaxRecursionDepth) {
4170  return WasmInitExpr(int32_t{0});
4171  }
4172  // 50% to generate a constant, 50% to generate a binary operator.
4173  uint8_t choice = range.get<uint8_t>() % 6;
4174  switch (choice) {
4175  case 0:
4176  case 1:
4177  case 2:
4178  if (choice % 2 == 0 && builder->NumGlobals()) {
4179  // Search for a matching global to emit a global.get.
4180  int num_globals = builder->NumGlobals();
4181  int start_index = range.get<uint8_t>() % num_globals;
4182  for (int i = 0; i < num_globals; ++i) {
4183  int index = (start_index + i) % num_globals;
4184  if (builder->GetGlobalType(index) == type &&
4185  !builder->IsMutableGlobal(index)) {
4186  return WasmInitExpr::GlobalGet(index);
4187  }
4188  }
4189  // Fall back to constant if no matching global was found.
4190  }
4191  return WasmInitExpr(range.getPseudoRandom<int32_t>());
4192  default:
4193  WasmInitExpr::Operator op = choice == 3 ? WasmInitExpr::kI32Add
4194  : choice == 4 ? WasmInitExpr::kI32Sub
4195  : WasmInitExpr::kI32Mul;
4196  return WasmInitExpr::Binop(
4197  zone, op,
4198  GenerateInitExpr(zone, range, builder, kWasmI32, structs, arrays,
4199  recursion_depth + 1),
4200  GenerateInitExpr(zone, range, builder, kWasmI32, structs, arrays,
4201  recursion_depth + 1));
4202  }
4203  }
4204  case kI64: {
4205  if (range.size() == 0 || recursion_depth >= kMaxRecursionDepth) {
4206  return WasmInitExpr(int64_t{0});
4207  }
4208  // 50% to generate a constant, 50% to generate a binary operator.
4209  uint8_t choice = range.get<uint8_t>() % 6;
4210  switch (choice) {
4211  case 0:
4212  case 1:
4213  case 2:
4214  return WasmInitExpr(range.get<int64_t>());
4215  default:
4216  WasmInitExpr::Operator op = choice == 3 ? WasmInitExpr::kI64Add
4217  : choice == 4 ? WasmInitExpr::kI64Sub
4218  : WasmInitExpr::kI64Mul;
4219  return WasmInitExpr::Binop(
4220  zone, op,
4221  GenerateInitExpr(zone, range, builder, kWasmI64, structs, arrays,
4222  recursion_depth + 1),
4223  GenerateInitExpr(zone, range, builder, kWasmI64, structs, arrays,
4224  recursion_depth + 1));
4225  }
4226  }
4227  case kF16:
4228  case kF32:
4229  return WasmInitExpr(0.0f);
4230  case kF64:
4231  return WasmInitExpr(0.0);
4232  case kS128: {
4233  uint8_t s128_const[kSimd128Size] = {0};
4234  return WasmInitExpr(s128_const);
4235  }
4236  case kRefNull: {
4237  bool null_only = false;
4238  switch (type.heap_representation()) {
4239  case HeapType::kNone:
4240  case HeapType::kNoFunc:
4241  case HeapType::kNoExtern:
4242  null_only = true;
4243  break;
4244  default:
4245  break;
4246  }
4247  if (range.size() == 0 || recursion_depth >= kMaxRecursionDepth ||
4248  null_only || (range.get<uint8_t>() % 4 == 0)) {
4249  return WasmInitExpr::RefNullConst(type.heap_type());
4250  }
4251  [[fallthrough]];
4252  }
4253  case kRef: {
4254  switch (type.heap_representation()) {
4255  case HeapType::kStruct: {
4256  ModuleTypeIndex index =
4257  structs[range.get<uint8_t>() % structs.size()];
4258  return GenerateStructNewInitExpr(zone, range, builder, index, structs,
4259  arrays, recursion_depth);
4260  }
4261  case HeapType::kAny: {
4262  // Do not use 0 as the determining value here, otherwise an exhausted
4263  // {range} will generate an infinite recursion with the {kExtern}
4264  // case.
4265  if (recursion_depth < kMaxRecursionDepth && range.size() > 0 &&
4266  range.get<uint8_t>() % 4 == 3) {
4267  return WasmInitExpr::AnyConvertExtern(
4268  zone, GenerateInitExpr(zone, range, builder,
4269  ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
4270  kWasmExternRef, type.nullability()),
4271  structs, arrays, recursion_depth + 1));
4272  }
4273  [[fallthrough]];
4274  }
4275  case HeapType::kEq: {
4276  uint8_t choice = range.get<uint8_t>() % 3;
4277  HeapType subtype = choice == 0 ? kWasmI31Ref
4278  : choice == 1 ? kWasmArrayRef
4279  : kWasmStructRef;
4280 
4281  return GenerateInitExpr(
4282  zone, range, builder,
4283  ValueType::RefMaybeNull(subtype, type.nullability()), structs,
4284  arrays, recursion_depth);
4285  }
4286  case HeapType::kFunc: {
4287  uint32_t index =
4288  range.get<uint32_t>() % (builder->NumDeclaredFunctions() +
4289  builder->NumImportedFunctions());
4290  return WasmInitExpr::RefFuncConst(index);
4291  }
4292  case HeapType::kExtern:
4293  return WasmInitExpr::ExternConvertAny(
4294  zone, GenerateInitExpr(zone, range, builder,
4295  ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
4296  kWasmAnyRef, type.nullability()),
4297  structs, arrays, recursion_depth + 1));
4298  case HeapType::kI31:
4299  return WasmInitExpr::RefI31(
4300  zone, GenerateInitExpr(zone, range, builder, kWasmI32, structs,
4301  arrays, recursion_depth + 1));
4302  case HeapType::kArray: {
4303  ModuleTypeIndex index = arrays[range.get<uint8_t>() % arrays.size()];
4304  return GenerateArrayInitExpr(zone, range, builder, index, structs,
4305  arrays, recursion_depth);
4306  }
4307  case HeapType::kNone:
4308  case HeapType::kNoFunc:
4309  case HeapType::kNoExtern:
4310  UNREACHABLE();
4311  default: {
4312  ModuleTypeIndex index = type.ref_index();
4313  if (builder->IsStructType(index)) {
4314  return GenerateStructNewInitExpr(zone, range, builder, index,
4315  structs, arrays, recursion_depth);
4316  } else if (builder->IsArrayType(index)) {
4317  return GenerateArrayInitExpr(zone, range, builder, index, structs,
4318  arrays, recursion_depth);
4319  } else {
4320  DCHECK(builder->IsSignature(index));
4321  for (int i = 0; i < builder->NumDeclaredFunctions(); ++i) {
4322  if (builder->GetFunction(i)->sig_index() == index) {
4323  return WasmInitExpr::RefFuncConst(
4324  builder->NumImportedFunctions() + i);
4325  }
4326  }
4327  // There has to be at least one function per signature, otherwise
4328  // the init expression is unable to generate a non-nullable
4329  // reference with the correct type.
4330  UNREACHABLE();
4331  }
4332  UNREACHABLE();
4333  }
4334  }
4335  }
4336  case kVoid:
4337  case kTop:
4338  case kBottom:
4339  UNREACHABLE();
4340  }
4341 }
4342 
4343 } // namespace
4344 
4345 base::Vector<uint8_t> GenerateRandomWasmModule(
4346  Zone* zone, WasmModuleGenerationOptions options,
4347  base::Vector<const uint8_t> data) {
4348  WasmModuleBuilder builder(zone);
4349 
4350  // Split input data in two parts:
4351  // - One for the "module" (types, globals, ..)
4352  // - One for all the function bodies
4353  // This prevents using a too large portion on the module resulting in
4354  // uninteresting function bodies.
4355  DataRange module_range(data);
4356  DataRange functions_range = module_range.split();
4357  std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex> function_signatures;
4358 
4359  // At least 1 function is needed.
4360  int max_num_functions = MaxNumOfFunctions();
4361  CHECK_GE(max_num_functions, 1);
4362  uint8_t num_functions = 1 + (module_range.get<uint8_t>() % max_num_functions);
4363 
4364  // In case of WasmGC expressions:
4365  // Add struct and array types first so that we get a chance to generate
4366  // these types in function signatures.
4367  // Currently, `BodyGen` assumes this order for struct/array/signature
4368  // definitions.
4369  // Otherwise, for non-WasmGC we can't use structs/arrays.
4370  uint8_t num_structs = 0;
4371  uint8_t num_arrays = 0;
4372  std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex> array_types;
4373  std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex> struct_types;
4374 
4375  // In case of WasmGC expressions:
4376  // We always add two default array types with mutable i8 and i16 elements,
4377  // respectively.
4378  constexpr uint8_t kNumDefaultArrayTypesForWasmGC = 2;
4379  if (options.generate_wasm_gc()) {
4380  // We need at least one struct and one array in order to support
4381  // WasmInitExpr for abstract types.
4382  num_structs = 1 + module_range.get<uint8_t>() % kMaxStructs;
4383  num_arrays = kNumDefaultArrayTypesForWasmGC +
4384  module_range.get<uint8_t>() % kMaxArrays;
4385  }
4386 
4387  uint8_t num_signatures = num_functions;
4388  ModuleGen gen_module(zone, options, &builder, &module_range, num_functions,
4389  num_structs, num_arrays, num_signatures);
4390 
4391  // Add random number of memories.
4392  // TODO(v8:14674): Add a mode without declaring any memory or memory
4393  // instructions.
4394  gen_module.GenerateRandomMemories();
4395 
4396  uint8_t current_type_index = 0;
4397  // In case of WasmGC expressions, we create recursive groups for the recursive
4398  // types.
4399  std::map<uint8_t, uint8_t> explicit_rec_groups;
4400  if (options.generate_wasm_gc()) {
4401  // Put the types into random recursive groups.
4402  explicit_rec_groups = gen_module.GenerateRandomRecursiveGroups(
4403  kNumDefaultArrayTypesForWasmGC);
4404 
4405  // Add default array types.
4406  static constexpr ModuleTypeIndex kArrayI8{0};
4407  static constexpr ModuleTypeIndex kArrayI16{1};
4408  {
4409  ArrayType* a8 = zone->New<ArrayType>(kWasmI8, 1);
4410  CHECK_EQ(kArrayI8, builder.AddArrayType(a8, true, kNoSuperType));
4411  array_types.push_back(kArrayI8);
4412  ArrayType* a16 = zone->New<ArrayType>(kWasmI16, 1);
4413  CHECK_EQ(kArrayI16, builder.AddArrayType(a16, true, kNoSuperType));
4414  array_types.push_back(kArrayI16);
4415  }
4416  static_assert(kNumDefaultArrayTypesForWasmGC == kArrayI16.index + 1);
4417  current_type_index = kNumDefaultArrayTypesForWasmGC;
4418 
4419  // Add randomly generated structs.
4420  gen_module.GenerateRandomStructs(explicit_rec_groups, struct_types,
4421  current_type_index,
4422  kNumDefaultArrayTypesForWasmGC);
4423  DCHECK_EQ(current_type_index, kNumDefaultArrayTypesForWasmGC + num_structs);
4424 
4425  // Add randomly generated arrays.
4426  gen_module.GenerateRandomArrays(explicit_rec_groups, array_types,
4427  current_type_index);
4428  DCHECK_EQ(current_type_index, num_structs + num_arrays);
4429  }
4430 
4431  // We keep the signature for the first (main) function constant.
4432  constexpr bool kIsFinal = true;
4433  auto kMainFnSig = FixedSizeSignature<ValueType>::Returns(kWasmI32).Params(
4434  kWasmI32, kWasmI32, kWasmI32);
4435  function_signatures.push_back(
4436  builder.ForceAddSignature(&kMainFnSig, kIsFinal));
4437  current_type_index++;
4438 
4439  // Add randomly generated signatures.
4440  gen_module.GenerateRandomFunctionSigs(
4441  explicit_rec_groups, function_signatures, current_type_index, kIsFinal);
4442  DCHECK_EQ(current_type_index, num_functions + num_structs + num_arrays);
4443 
4444  // Add exceptions.
4445  int num_exceptions = 1 + (module_range.get<uint8_t>() % kMaxExceptions);
4446  gen_module.GenerateRandomExceptions(num_exceptions);
4447 
4448  // In case of WasmGC expressions:
4449  // Add the "wasm:js-string" imports to the module. They may or may not be
4450  // used later, but they'll always be available.
4451  StringImports strings = options.generate_wasm_gc()
4452  ? gen_module.AddImportedStringImports()
4453  : StringImports();
4454 
4455  // Generate function declarations before tables. This will be needed once we
4456  // have typed-function tables.
4457  std::vector<WasmFunctionBuilder*> functions;
4458  functions.reserve(num_functions);
4459  for (uint8_t i = 0; i < num_functions; i++) {
4460  // If we are using wasm-gc, we cannot allow signature normalization
4461  // performed by adding a function by {FunctionSig}, because we emit
4462  // everything in one recursive group which blocks signature
4463  // canonicalization.
4464  // TODO(14034): Relax this when we implement proper recursive-group
4465  // support.
4466  functions.push_back(builder.AddFunction(function_signatures[i]));
4467  }
4468 
4469  // Generate tables before function bodies, so they are available for table
4470  // operations. Generate tables before the globals, so tables don't
4471  // accidentally use globals in their initializer expressions.
4472  // Always generate at least one table for call_indirect.
4473  gen_module.GenerateRandomTables(array_types, struct_types);
4474 
4475  // Add globals.
4476  auto [globals, mutable_globals] =
4477  gen_module.GenerateRandomGlobals(array_types, struct_types);
4478 
4479  // Add passive data segments.
4480  int num_data_segments = module_range.get<uint8_t>() % kMaxPassiveDataSegments;
4481  for (int i = 0; i < num_data_segments; i++) {
4482  GeneratePassiveDataSegment(&module_range, &builder);
4483  }
4484 
4485  // Generate function bodies.
4486  for (int i = 0; i < num_functions; ++i) {
4487  WasmFunctionBuilder* f = functions[i];
4488  // On the last function don't split the DataRange but just use the
4489  // existing DataRange.
4490  DataRange function_range = i != num_functions - 1
4491  ? functions_range.split()
4492  : std::move(functions_range);
4493  BodyGen gen_body(options, f, function_signatures, globals, mutable_globals,
4494  struct_types, array_types, strings, &function_range);
4495  const FunctionSig* sig = f->signature();
4496  base::Vector<const ValueType> return_types(sig->returns().begin(),
4497  sig->return_count());
4498  gen_body.InitializeNonDefaultableLocals(&function_range);
4499  gen_body.Generate(return_types, &function_range);
4500  f->Emit(kExprEnd);
4501  if (i == 0) builder.AddExport(base::CStrVector("main"), f);
4502  }
4503 
4504  ZoneBuffer buffer{zone};
4505  builder.WriteTo(&buffer);
4506  return base::VectorOf(buffer);
4507 }
4508 
4509 // Used by the initializer expression fuzzer.
4510 base::Vector<uint8_t> GenerateWasmModuleForInitExpressions(
4511  Zone* zone, base::Vector<const uint8_t> data, size_t* count) {
4512  // Don't limit expressions for the initializer expression fuzzer.
4513  constexpr WasmModuleGenerationOptions options =
4514  WasmModuleGenerationOptions::All();
4515  WasmModuleBuilder builder(zone);
4516 
4517  DataRange module_range(data);
4518  std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex> function_signatures;
4519  std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex> array_types;
4520  std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex> struct_types;
4521 
4522  int num_globals = 1 + module_range.get<uint8_t>() % (kMaxGlobals + 1);
4523 
4524  uint8_t num_functions = num_globals;
4525  *count = num_functions;
4526 
4527  // We need at least one struct and one array in order to support
4528  // WasmInitExpr for abstract types.
4529  uint8_t num_structs = 1 + module_range.get<uint8_t>() % kMaxStructs;
4530  uint8_t num_arrays = 1 + module_range.get<uint8_t>() % kMaxArrays;
4531  uint16_t num_types = num_functions + num_structs + num_arrays;
4532 
4533  uint8_t current_type_index = 0;
4534 
4535  // Add random-generated types.
4536  uint8_t last_struct_type = current_type_index + num_structs;
4537  for (; current_type_index < last_struct_type; current_type_index++) {
4538  ModuleTypeIndex supertype = kNoSuperType;
4539  uint8_t num_fields = module_range.get<uint8_t>() % (kMaxStructFields + 1);
4540 
4541  uint32_t existing_struct_types = current_type_index;
4542  if (existing_struct_types > 0 && module_range.get<bool>()) {
4543  supertype =
4544  ModuleTypeIndex{module_range.get<uint8_t>() % existing_struct_types};
4545  num_fields += builder.GetStructType(supertype)->field_count();
4546  }
4547  // TODO(403372470): Add support for custom descriptors.
4548  // TODO(42204563): Add support for shared structs.
4549  StructType::Builder struct_builder(zone, num_fields, false, false);
4550 
4551  // Add all fields from super type.
4552  uint32_t field_index = 0;
4553  if (supertype != kNoSuperType) {
4554  const StructType* parent = builder.GetStructType(supertype);
4555  for (; field_index < parent->field_count(); ++field_index) {
4556  struct_builder.AddField(parent->field(field_index),
4557  parent->mutability(field_index));
4558  }
4559  }
4560  for (; field_index < num_fields; field_index++) {
4561  ValueType type = GetValueTypeHelper(
4562  options, &module_range, current_type_index, current_type_index,
4563  kIncludeNumericTypes, kIncludePackedTypes, kExcludeSomeGenerics);
4564  // To prevent huge initializer expressions, limit the existence of
4565  // non-nullable references to the first 2 struct types (for non-inherited
4566  // fields).
4567  if (current_type_index >= 2 && type.is_non_nullable()) {
4568  type = type.AsNullable();
4569  }
4570 
4571  bool mutability = module_range.get<bool>();
4572  struct_builder.AddField(type, mutability);
4573  }
4574  StructType* struct_fuz = struct_builder.Build();
4575  ModuleTypeIndex index = builder.AddStructType(struct_fuz, false, supertype);
4576  struct_types.push_back(index);
4577  }
4578 
4579  for (; current_type_index < num_structs + num_arrays; current_type_index++) {
4580  ValueType type = GetValueTypeHelper(
4581  options, &module_range, current_type_index, current_type_index,
4582  kIncludeNumericTypes, kIncludePackedTypes, kExcludeSomeGenerics);
4583  ModuleTypeIndex supertype = kNoSuperType;
4584  if (current_type_index > last_struct_type && module_range.get<bool>()) {
4585  uint32_t existing_array_types = current_type_index - last_struct_type;
4586  supertype =
4587  ModuleTypeIndex{last_struct_type +
4588  (module_range.get<uint8_t>() % existing_array_types)};
4589  type = builder.GetArrayType(supertype)->element_type();
4590  }
4591  ArrayType* array_fuz = zone->New<ArrayType>(type, true);
4592  ModuleTypeIndex index = builder.AddArrayType(array_fuz, false, supertype);
4593  array_types.push_back(index);
4594  }
4595 
4596  // Choose global types and create function signatures.
4597  constexpr bool kIsFinal = true;
4598  std::vector<ValueType> globals;
4599  for (; current_type_index < num_types; current_type_index++) {
4600  ValueType return_type = GetValueTypeHelper(
4601  options, &module_range, num_types - num_globals,
4602  num_types - num_globals, kIncludeNumericTypes, kExcludePackedTypes,
4603  kIncludeAllGenerics, kExcludeS128);
4604  globals.push_back(return_type);
4605  // Create a new function signature for each global. These functions will be
4606  // used to compare against the initializer value of the global.
4607  FunctionSig::Builder sig_builder(zone, 1, 0);
4608  sig_builder.AddReturn(return_type);
4609  ModuleTypeIndex signature_index =
4610  builder.ForceAddSignature(sig_builder.Get(), kIsFinal);
4611  function_signatures.push_back(signature_index);
4612  }
4613 
4614  std::vector<WasmFunctionBuilder*> functions;
4615  functions.reserve(num_functions);
4616  for (uint8_t i = 0; i < num_functions; i++) {
4617  functions.push_back(builder.AddFunction(function_signatures[i]));
4618  }
4619 
4620  // Create globals.
4621  std::vector<uint8_t> mutable_globals;
4622  std::vector<WasmInitExpr> init_exprs;
4623  init_exprs.reserve(num_globals);
4624  mutable_globals.reserve(num_globals);
4625  CHECK_EQ(globals.size(), num_globals);
4626  uint64_t mutabilities = module_range.get<uint64_t>();
4627  for (int i = 0; i < num_globals; ++i) {
4628  ValueType type = globals[i];
4629  // 50% of globals are immutable.
4630  const bool mutability = mutabilities & 1;
4631  mutabilities >>= 1;
4632  WasmInitExpr init_expr = GenerateInitExpr(
4633  zone, module_range, &builder, type, struct_types, array_types, 0);
4634  init_exprs.push_back(init_expr);
4635  auto buffer = zone->AllocateVector<char>(8);
4636  size_t len = base::SNPrintF(buffer, "g%i", i);
4637  builder.AddExportedGlobal(type, mutability, init_expr,
4638  {buffer.begin(), len});
4639  if (mutability) mutable_globals.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(i));
4640  }
4641 
4642  // Create functions containing the initializer of each global as its function
4643  // body.
4644  for (int i = 0; i < num_functions; ++i) {
4645  WasmFunctionBuilder* f = functions[i];
4646  f->EmitFromInitializerExpression(init_exprs[i]);
4647  auto buffer = zone->AllocateVector<char>(8);
4648  size_t len = base::SNPrintF(buffer, "f%i", i);
4649  builder.AddExport({buffer.begin(), len}, f);
4650  }
4651 
4652  ZoneBuffer buffer{zone};
4653  builder.WriteTo(&buffer);
4654  return base::VectorOf(buffer);
4655 }
4656 
4657 namespace {
4658 
4659 bool HasSameReturns(const FunctionSig* a, const FunctionSig* b) {
4660  if (a->return_count() != b->return_count()) return false;
4661  for (size_t i = 0; i < a->return_count(); ++i) {
4662  if (a->GetReturn(i) != b->GetReturn(i)) return false;
4663  }
4664  return true;
4665 }
4666 
4667 void EmitDeoptAndReturnValues(BodyGen gen_body, WasmFunctionBuilder* f,
4668  const FunctionSig* target_sig,
4669  ModuleTypeIndex target_sig_index,
4670  uint32_t global_index, uint32_t table_index,
4671  bool use_table64, DataRange* data) {
4672  base::Vector<const ValueType> return_types = f->signature()->returns();
4673  // Split the return types randomly and generate some values before the
4674  // deopting call and some afterwards. (This makes sure that we have deopts
4675  // where there are values on the wasm value stack which are not used by the
4676  // deopting call itself.)
4677  uint32_t returns_split = data->get<uint8_t>() % (return_types.size() + 1);
4678  if (returns_split) {
4679  gen_body.Generate(return_types.SubVector(0, returns_split), data);
4680  }
4681  gen_body.Generate(target_sig->parameters(), data);
4682  f->EmitWithU32V(kExprGlobalGet, global_index);
4683  if (use_table64) {
4684  f->Emit(kExprI64UConvertI32);
4685  }
4686  // Tail calls can only be emitted if the return types match.
4687  bool same_returns = HasSameReturns(target_sig, f->signature());
4688  size_t option_count = (same_returns + 1) * 2;
4689  switch (data->get<uint8_t>() % option_count) {
4690  case 0:
4691  // Emit call_ref.
4692  f->Emit(kExprTableGet);
4693  f->EmitU32V(table_index);
4694  f->EmitWithPrefix(kExprRefCast);
4695  f->EmitI32V(target_sig_index);
4696  f->EmitWithU32V(kExprCallRef, target_sig_index);
4697  break;
4698  case 1:
4699  // Emit call_indirect.
4700  f->EmitWithU32V(kExprCallIndirect, target_sig_index);
4701  f->EmitByte(table_index);
4702  break;
4703  case 2:
4704  // Emit return_call_ref.
4705  f->Emit(kExprTableGet);
4706  f->EmitU32V(table_index);
4707  f->EmitWithPrefix(kExprRefCast);
4708  f->EmitI32V(target_sig_index);
4709  f->EmitWithU32V(kExprReturnCallRef, target_sig_index);
4710  break;
4711  case 3:
4712  // Emit return_call_indirect.
4713  f->EmitWithU32V(kExprReturnCallIndirect, target_sig_index);
4714  f->EmitByte(table_index);
4715  break;
4716  default:
4717  UNREACHABLE();
4718  }
4719  gen_body.ConsumeAndGenerate(target_sig->returns(),
4720  return_types.SubVectorFrom(returns_split), data);
4721 }
4722 
4723 void EmitCallAndReturnValues(BodyGen gen_body, WasmFunctionBuilder* f,
4724  WasmFunctionBuilder* callee, uint32_t table_index,
4725  bool use_table64, DataRange* data) {
4726  const FunctionSig* callee_sig = callee->signature();
4727  uint32_t callee_index =
4728  callee->func_index() + gen_body.NumImportedFunctions();
4729 
4730  base::Vector<const ValueType> return_types = f->signature()->returns();
4731  // Split the return types randomly and generate some values before the
4732  // deopting call and some afterwards to create more interesting test cases.
4733  uint32_t returns_split = data->get<uint8_t>() % (return_types.size() + 1);
4734  if (returns_split) {
4735  gen_body.Generate(return_types.SubVector(0, returns_split), data);
4736  }
4737  gen_body.Generate(callee_sig->parameters(), data);
4738  // Tail calls can only be emitted if the return types match.
4739  bool same_returns = HasSameReturns(callee_sig, f->signature());
4740  size_t option_count = (same_returns + 1) * 3;
4741  switch (data->get<uint8_t>() % option_count) {
4742  case 0:
4743  f->EmitWithU32V(kExprCallFunction, callee_index);
4744  break;
4745  case 1:
4746  f->EmitWithU32V(kExprRefFunc, callee_index);
4747  f->EmitWithU32V(kExprCallRef, callee->sig_index());
4748  break;
4749  case 2:
4750  // Note that this assumes that the declared function index is the same as
4751  // the index of the function in the table.
4752  use_table64 ? f->EmitI64Const(callee->func_index())
4753  : f->EmitI32Const(callee->func_index());
4754  f->EmitWithU32V(kExprCallIndirect, callee->sig_index());
4755  f->EmitByte(table_index);
4756  break;
4757  case 3:
4758  f->EmitWithU32V(kExprReturnCall, callee_index);
4759  break;
4760  case 4:
4761  f->EmitWithU32V(kExprRefFunc, callee_index);
4762  f->EmitWithU32V(kExprReturnCallRef, callee->sig_index());
4763  break;
4764  case 5:
4765  // Note that this assumes that the declared function index is the same as
4766  // the index of the function in the table.
4767  use_table64 ? f->EmitI64Const(callee->func_index())
4768  : f->EmitI32Const(callee->func_index());
4769  f->EmitWithU32V(kExprReturnCallIndirect, callee->sig_index());
4770  f->EmitByte(table_index);
4771  break;
4772  default:
4773  UNREACHABLE();
4774  }
4775  gen_body.ConsumeAndGenerate(callee_sig->returns(),
4776  return_types.SubVectorFrom(returns_split), data);
4777 }
4778 } // anonymous namespace
4779 
4780 base::Vector<uint8_t> GenerateWasmModuleForDeopt(
4781  Zone* zone, base::Vector<const uint8_t> data,
4782  std::vector<std::string>& callees, std::vector<std::string>& inlinees) {
4783  // Don't limit the features for the deopt fuzzer.
4784  constexpr WasmModuleGenerationOptions options =
4785  WasmModuleGenerationOptions::All();
4786  WasmModuleBuilder builder(zone);
4787 
4788  DataRange range(data);
4789  std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex> function_signatures;
4790  std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex> array_types;
4791  std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex> struct_types;
4792 
4793  const int kMaxCallTargets = 5;
4794  const int kMaxInlinees = 3;
4795 
4796  // We need at least 2 call targets to be able to trigger a deopt.
4797  const int num_call_targets = 2 + range.get<uint8_t>() % (kMaxCallTargets - 1);
4798  const int num_inlinees = range.get<uint8_t>() % (kMaxInlinees + 1);
4799 
4800  // 1 main function + x inlinees + x callees.
4801  uint8_t num_functions = 1 + num_inlinees + num_call_targets;
4802  // 1 signature for all the callees, 1 signature for the main function +
4803  // 1 signature per inlinee.
4804  uint8_t num_signatures = 2 + num_inlinees;
4805 
4806  uint8_t num_structs = 1 + range.get<uint8_t>() % kMaxStructs;
4807  // In case of WasmGC expressions:
4808  // We always add two default array types with mutable i8 and i16 elements,
4809  // respectively.
4810  constexpr uint8_t kNumDefaultArrayTypesForWasmGC = 2;
4811  uint8_t num_arrays =
4812  range.get<uint8_t>() % kMaxArrays + kNumDefaultArrayTypesForWasmGC;
4813  // Just ignoring user-defined signature types in the signatures.
4814  uint16_t num_types = num_structs + num_arrays;
4815 
4816  uint8_t current_type_index = kNumDefaultArrayTypesForWasmGC;
4817 
4818  // Add random-generated types.
4819  ModuleGen gen_module(zone, options, &builder, &range, num_functions,
4820  num_structs, num_arrays, num_signatures);
4821 
4822  gen_module.GenerateRandomMemories();
4823  std::map<uint8_t, uint8_t> explicit_rec_groups =
4824  gen_module.GenerateRandomRecursiveGroups(kNumDefaultArrayTypesForWasmGC);
4825  // Add default array types.
4826  static constexpr ModuleTypeIndex kArrayI8{0};
4827  static constexpr ModuleTypeIndex kArrayI16{1};
4828  {
4829  ArrayType* a8 = zone->New<ArrayType>(kWasmI8, true);
4830  CHECK_EQ(kArrayI8, builder.AddArrayType(a8, true, kNoSuperType));
4831  array_types.push_back(kArrayI8);
4832  ArrayType* a16 = zone->New<ArrayType>(kWasmI16, true);
4833  CHECK_EQ(kArrayI16, builder.AddArrayType(a16, true, kNoSuperType));
4834  array_types.push_back(kArrayI16);
4835  }
4836  static_assert(kNumDefaultArrayTypesForWasmGC == kArrayI16.index + 1);
4837  gen_module.GenerateRandomStructs(explicit_rec_groups, struct_types,
4838  current_type_index,
4839  kNumDefaultArrayTypesForWasmGC);
4840  DCHECK_EQ(current_type_index, kNumDefaultArrayTypesForWasmGC + num_structs);
4841  gen_module.GenerateRandomArrays(explicit_rec_groups, array_types,
4842  current_type_index);
4843  DCHECK_EQ(current_type_index, num_structs + num_arrays);
4844 
4845  // Create signature for call target.
4846  std::vector<ValueType> return_types =
4847  GenerateTypes(options, &range, num_types);
4848  constexpr bool kIsFinal = true;
4849  const FunctionSig* target_sig = CreateSignature(
4850  builder.zone(), base::VectorOf(GenerateTypes(options, &range, num_types)),
4851  base::VectorOf(return_types));
4852  ModuleTypeIndex target_sig_index =
4853  builder.ForceAddSignature(target_sig, kIsFinal);
4854 
4855  function_signatures.reserve(num_call_targets);
4856  for (int i = 0; i < num_call_targets; ++i) {
4857  // Simplification: All call targets of a call_ref / call_indirect have the
4858  // same signature.
4859  function_signatures.push_back(target_sig_index);
4860  }
4861 
4862  // Create signatures for inlinees.
4863  // Use the same return types with a certain chance. This increases the chance
4864  // to emit return calls.
4865  uint8_t use_same_return = range.get<uint8_t>();
4866  for (int i = 0; i < num_inlinees; ++i) {
4867  if ((use_same_return & (1 << i)) == 0) {
4868  return_types = GenerateTypes(options, &range, num_types);
4869  }
4870  const FunctionSig* inlinee_sig = CreateSignature(
4871  builder.zone(),
4872  base::VectorOf(GenerateTypes(options, &range, num_types)),
4873  base::VectorOf(return_types));
4874  function_signatures.push_back(
4875  builder.ForceAddSignature(inlinee_sig, kIsFinal));
4876  }
4877 
4878  // Create signature for main function.
4879  const FunctionSig* main_sig =
4880  CreateSignature(builder.zone(), base::VectorOf({ValueType{kWasmI32}}),
4881  base::VectorOf({ValueType{kWasmI32}}));
4882  function_signatures.push_back(builder.ForceAddSignature(main_sig, kIsFinal));
4883 
4884  DCHECK_EQ(function_signatures.back().index,
4885  num_structs + num_arrays + num_signatures - 1);
4886 
4887  // This needs to be done after the signatures are added.
4888  int num_exceptions = 1 + range.get<uint8_t>() % kMaxExceptions;
4889  gen_module.GenerateRandomExceptions(num_exceptions);
4890  StringImports strings = gen_module.AddImportedStringImports();
4891 
4892  // Add functions to module.
4893  std::vector<WasmFunctionBuilder*> functions;
4894  DCHECK_EQ(num_functions, function_signatures.size());
4895  functions.reserve(num_functions);
4896  for (uint8_t i = 0; i < num_functions; i++) {
4897  functions.push_back(builder.AddFunction(function_signatures[i]));
4898  }
4899 
4900  uint32_t num_entries = num_call_targets + num_inlinees;
4901  bool use_table64 = range.get<bool>();
4902  AddressType address_type =
4903  use_table64 ? AddressType::kI64 : AddressType::kI32;
4904  uint32_t table_index =
4905  builder.AddTable(kWasmFuncRef, num_entries, num_entries, address_type);
4906  WasmModuleBuilder::WasmElemSegment segment(
4907  zone, kWasmFuncRef, table_index,
4908  use_table64 ? WasmInitExpr(int64_t{0}) : WasmInitExpr(0));
4909  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < num_entries; i++) {
4910  segment.entries.emplace_back(
4911  WasmModuleBuilder::WasmElemSegment::Entry::kRefFuncEntry,
4912  builder.NumImportedFunctions() + i);
4913  }
4914  builder.AddElementSegment(std::move(segment));
4915 
4916  gen_module.GenerateRandomTables(array_types, struct_types);
4917 
4918  // Create global for call target index.
4919  // Simplification: This global is used to specify the call target at the deopt
4920  // point instead of passing the call target around dynamically.
4921  uint32_t global_index =
4922  builder.AddExportedGlobal(kWasmI32, true, WasmInitExpr(0),
4923  base::StaticCharVector("call_target_index"));
4924 
4925  // Create inlinee bodies.
4926  for (int i = 0; i < num_inlinees; ++i) {
4927  uint32_t declared_func_index = i + num_call_targets;
4928  WasmFunctionBuilder* f = functions[declared_func_index];
4929  DataRange function_range = range.split();
4930  BodyGen gen_body(options, f, function_signatures, {}, {}, struct_types,
4931  array_types, strings, &function_range);
4932  gen_body.InitializeNonDefaultableLocals(&function_range);
4933  if (i == 0) {
4934  // For the inner-most inlinee, emit the deopt point (e.g. a call_ref).
4935  EmitDeoptAndReturnValues(gen_body, f, target_sig, target_sig_index,
4936  global_index, table_index, use_table64,
4937  &function_range);
4938  } else {
4939  // All other inlinees call the previous inlinee.
4940  uint32_t callee_declared_index = declared_func_index - 1;
4941  EmitCallAndReturnValues(gen_body, f, functions[callee_declared_index],
4942  table_index, use_table64, &function_range);
4943  }
4944  f->Emit(kExprEnd);
4945  auto buffer = zone->AllocateVector<char>(32);
4946  size_t len = base::SNPrintF(buffer, "inlinee_%i", i);
4947  builder.AddExport({buffer.begin(), len}, f);
4948  inlinees.emplace_back(buffer.begin(), len);
4949  }
4950 
4951  // Create main function body.
4952  {
4953  uint32_t declared_func_index = num_functions - 1;
4954  WasmFunctionBuilder* f = functions[declared_func_index];
4955  DataRange function_range = range.split();
4956  BodyGen gen_body(options, f, function_signatures, {}, {}, struct_types,
4957  array_types, strings, &function_range);
4958  gen_body.InitializeNonDefaultableLocals(&function_range);
4959  // Store the call target
4960  f->EmitWithU32V(kExprLocalGet, 0);
4961  f->EmitWithU32V(kExprGlobalSet, 0);
4962  // Call inlinee or emit deopt.
4963  if (num_inlinees == 0) {
4964  // If we don't have any inlinees, directly emit the deopt point.
4965  EmitDeoptAndReturnValues(gen_body, f, target_sig, target_sig_index,
4966  global_index, table_index, use_table64,
4967  &function_range);
4968  } else {
4969  // Otherwise call the "outer-most" inlinee.
4970  uint32_t callee_declared_index = declared_func_index - 1;
4971  EmitCallAndReturnValues(gen_body, f, functions[callee_declared_index],
4972  table_index, use_table64, &function_range);
4973  }
4974 
4975  f->Emit(kExprEnd);
4976  builder.AddExport(base::StaticCharVector("main"), f);
4977  }
4978 
4979  // Create call target bodies.
4980  // This is done last as we care much less about the content of these
4981  // functions, so it's less of an issue if there aren't (m)any random bytes
4982  // left.
4983  for (int i = 0; i < num_call_targets; ++i) {
4984  WasmFunctionBuilder* f = functions[i];
4985  DataRange function_range = range.split();
4986  BodyGen gen_body(options, f, function_signatures, {}, {}, struct_types,
4987  array_types, strings, &function_range);
4988  const FunctionSig* sig = f->signature();
4989  base::Vector<const ValueType> target_return_types(sig->returns().begin(),
4990  sig->return_count());
4991  gen_body.InitializeNonDefaultableLocals(&function_range);
4992  gen_body.Generate(target_return_types, &function_range);
4993 
4994  f->Emit(kExprEnd);
4995  auto buffer = zone->AllocateVector<char>(32);
4996  size_t len = base::SNPrintF(buffer, "callee_%i", i);
4997  builder.AddExport({buffer.begin(), len}, f);
4998  callees.emplace_back(buffer.begin(), len);
4999  }
5000 
5001  ZoneBuffer buffer{zone};
5002  builder.WriteTo(&buffer);
5003  return base::VectorOf(buffer);
5004 }
5005 
5006 base::Vector<uint8_t> GenerateWasmModuleForRevec(
5007  Zone* zone, base::Vector<const uint8_t> data) {
5008  constexpr WasmModuleGenerationOptions options = {
5009  {WasmModuleGenerationOption::kGenerateSIMD}};
5010  WasmModuleBuilder builder(zone);
5011 
5012  // Split input data in two parts:
5013  // - One for the "module" (types, globals, ..)
5014  // - One for all the function bodies
5015  // This prevents using a too large portion on the module resulting in
5016  // uninteresting function bodies.
5017  DataRange module_range(data);
5018  DataRange functions_range = module_range.split();
5019  std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex> function_signatures;
5020 
5021  // At least 1 function is needed.
5022  int max_num_functions = MaxNumOfFunctions();
5023  CHECK_GE(max_num_functions, 1);
5024  uint8_t num_functions = 1 + (module_range.get<uint8_t>() % max_num_functions);
5025 
5026  constexpr uint8_t kNumStructs = 0;
5027  constexpr uint8_t kNumArrays = 0;
5028  constexpr uint16_t kNumTypes = kNumStructs + kNumArrays;
5029  std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex> array_types;
5030  std::vector<ModuleTypeIndex> struct_types;
5031 
5032  uint8_t num_signatures = num_functions;
5033  ModuleGen gen_module(zone, options, &builder, &module_range, num_functions,
5034  kNumStructs, kNumArrays, num_signatures);
5035 
5036  gen_module.GenerateRandomMemories();
5037 
5038  // We keep the signature for the first (main) function constant.
5039  constexpr bool kIsFinal = true;
5040  auto kMainFnSig = FixedSizeSignature<ValueType>::Returns(kWasmI32).Params(
5041  kWasmI32, kWasmI32, kWasmI32);
5042  function_signatures.push_back(
5043  builder.ForceAddSignature(&kMainFnSig, kIsFinal));
5044 
5045  // Other function signatures: return void with random params.
5046  constexpr base::Vector<const ValueType> kNoReturnType;
5047  for (int i = 1; i < num_signatures; ++i) {
5048  const FunctionSig* function_sig = CreateSignature(
5049  builder.zone(),
5050  base::VectorOf(GenerateTypes(options, &module_range, kNumTypes)),
5051  kNoReturnType);
5052  function_signatures.push_back(
5053  builder.ForceAddSignature(function_sig, kIsFinal));
5054  }
5055 
5056  // Add exceptions.
5057  int num_exceptions = 1 + (module_range.get<uint8_t>() % kMaxExceptions);
5058  gen_module.GenerateRandomExceptions(num_exceptions);
5059 
5060  StringImports strings = StringImports();
5061 
5062  // Generate function declarations before tables. This will be needed once we
5063  // have typed-function tables.
5064  std::vector<WasmFunctionBuilder*> functions;
5065  functions.reserve(num_functions);
5066  for (uint8_t i = 0; i < num_functions; i++) {
5067  functions.push_back(builder.AddFunction(function_signatures[i]));
5068  }
5069 
5070  gen_module.GenerateRandomTables(array_types, struct_types);
5071 
5072  // Add globals.
5073  auto [globals, mutable_globals] =
5074  gen_module.GenerateRandomGlobals(array_types, struct_types);
5075 
5076  // Add passive data segments.
5077  int num_data_segments = module_range.get<uint8_t>() % kMaxPassiveDataSegments;
5078  for (int i = 0; i < num_data_segments; i++) {
5079  GeneratePassiveDataSegment(&module_range, &builder);
5080  }
5081 
5082  // Generate function bodies.
5083  // Revec uses two contiguous S128Store instructions as seeds, the two
5084  // instructions share the same memory_index/alignment/index, the values to be
5085  // stored should be generated from the same DataRange. The second offset is 16
5086  // bytes larger than the first offset.
5087  for (int i = 0; i < num_functions; ++i) {
5088  WasmFunctionBuilder* f = functions[i];
5089  // On the last function don't split the DataRange but just use the
5090  // existing DataRange.
5091  DataRange function_range = i != num_functions - 1
5092  ? functions_range.split()
5093  : std::move(functions_range);
5094  BodyGen gen_body(options, f, function_signatures, globals, mutable_globals,
5095  struct_types, array_types, strings, &function_range);
5096  const FunctionSig* sig = f->signature();
5097  base::Vector<const ValueType> return_types(sig->returns().begin(),
5098  sig->return_count());
5099  gen_body.InitializeNonDefaultableLocals(&function_range);
5100 
5101  // Atomic operations need to be aligned exactly to their max alignment.
5102  const uint8_t align = function_range.getPseudoRandom<uint8_t>() % (4 + 1);
5103 
5104  // Only memory0 is supported in revec for now.
5105  constexpr uint8_t kMemoryIndex0 = 0;
5106 
5107  uint64_t offset = function_range.get<uint16_t>();
5108  // With a 1/256 chance generate potentially very large offsets.
5109  if ((offset & 0xff) == 0xff) {
5110  offset = f->builder()->IsMemory64(kMemoryIndex0)
5111  ? function_range.getPseudoRandom<uint64_t>() & 0x1ffffffff
5112  : function_range.getPseudoRandom<uint32_t>();
5113  }
5114 
5115  auto first_data = function_range.split();
5116 
5117  // === The first store. ===
5118  // Generate the index.
5119  uint32_t index;
5120  if (f->builder()->IsMemory64(kMemoryIndex0)) {
5121  index = f->AddLocal(kWasmI64);
5122  gen_body.Generate<kI64>(&first_data);
5123  } else {
5124  index = f->AddLocal(kWasmI32);
5125  gen_body.Generate<kI32>(&first_data);
5126  }
5127  f->EmitTeeLocal(index);
5128 
5129  // Generate the S128 value to be stored.
5130  // With 50% chance generated from the same sequence.
5131  DataRange store2_range = function_range.get<bool>()
5132  ? function_range.clone()
5133  : function_range.split();
5134 
5135  gen_body.Generate<kS128>(&function_range);
5136 
5137  // Format of the instruction (supports multi-memory):
5138  // memory_op (align | 0x40) memory_index offset
5139  f->EmitWithPrefix(kExprS128StoreMem);
5140  f->EmitU32V(align | 0x40);
5141  f->EmitU32V(kMemoryIndex0);
5142  f->EmitU64V(offset);
5143 
5144  // === The second store. ===
5145  // Share the same index, value generated from same
5146  // DataRange and offset is 16 larger.
5147  f->EmitGetLocal(index);
5148  gen_body.Generate<kS128>(&store2_range);
5149 
5150  f->EmitWithPrefix(kExprS128StoreMem);
5151  f->EmitU32V(align | 0x40);
5152  f->EmitU32V(kMemoryIndex0);
5153 
5154  uint64_t offset2;
5155  // offset + 16 shouldn't exceed the 32-bit range.
5156  if (!f->builder()->IsMemory64(kMemoryIndex0) &&
5157  offset + 16 >= std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max()) {
5158  offset2 = offset - 16;
5159  } else {
5160  offset2 = offset + 16;
5161  }
5162  f->EmitU64V(offset2);
5163 
5164  // int32_t main(int32_t, int32_t, int32_t)
5165  // S128 a = load(index + offset)
5166  // S128 b = load(index + offset2)
5167  // S128 c = a ^ b
5168  // return lane(c, 0) ^ lane(c, 1) ^ lane(c, 2) ^ lane(c, 3)
5169  if (i == 0) {
5170  // a = load(index + offset)
5171  f->EmitGetLocal(index);
5172  f->EmitWithPrefix(kExprS128LoadMem);
5173  f->EmitU32V(align | 0x40);
5174  f->EmitU32V(kMemoryIndex0);
5175  f->EmitU64V(offset);
5176 
5177  // b = load(index + offset2)
5178  f->EmitGetLocal(index);
5179  f->EmitWithPrefix(kExprS128LoadMem);
5180  f->EmitU32V(align | 0x40);
5181  f->EmitU32V(kMemoryIndex0);
5182  f->EmitU64V(offset2);
5183 
5184  // c = a ^ b
5185  f->EmitWithPrefix(kExprS128Xor);
5186 
5187  uint32_t xor_result = f->AddLocal(kWasmS128);
5188  f->EmitTeeLocal(xor_result);
5189  f->EmitWithPrefix(kExprI32x4ExtractLane);
5190  f->EmitByte(0);
5191 
5192  f->EmitGetLocal(xor_result);
5193  f->EmitWithPrefix(kExprI32x4ExtractLane);
5194  f->EmitByte(1);
5195 
5196  // lane(c, 0) ^ lane(c, 1)
5197  f->Emit(kExprI32Xor);
5198 
5199  f->EmitGetLocal(xor_result);
5200  f->EmitWithPrefix(kExprI32x4ExtractLane);
5201  f->EmitByte(2);
5202 
5203  f->EmitGetLocal(xor_result);
5204  f->EmitWithPrefix(kExprI32x4ExtractLane);
5205  f->EmitByte(3);
5206 
5207  // lane(c, 2) ^ lane(c, 3)
5208  f->Emit(kExprI32Xor);
5209 
5210  // lane(c, 0) ^ lane(c, 1) ^ lane(c, 2) ^ lane(c, 3)
5211  f->Emit(kExprI32Xor);
5212  }
5213 
5214  f->Emit(kExprEnd);
5215  if (i == 0) builder.AddExport(base::CStrVector("main"), f);
5216  }
5217 
5218  ZoneBuffer buffer{zone};
5219  builder.WriteTo(&buffer);
5220  return base::VectorOf(buffer);
5221 }
5222 
5223 } // namespace v8::internal::wasm::fuzzing
